rather than mere curiosity,

478
00:22:12,497 --> 00:22:14,207
and then we talked briefly.

479
00:22:16,877 --> 00:22:20,505
I feel like we haven't had
a chance to talk properly.

480
00:22:20,589 --> 00:22:22,799
So if you're okay with it,

481
00:22:22,883 --> 00:22:25,719
we should talk later,
even if it's not a three-way date.

482
00:22:25,802 --> 00:22:28,055
- Like this evening, when we get back?
- Uh-huh, this evening.

483
00:22:28,138 --> 00:22:29,139
Mm-hmm. Okay.

484
00:22:29,222 --> 00:22:30,349
- Okay.
- Okay.

485
00:22:30,432 --> 00:22:31,433
Good.

486
00:22:31,516 --> 00:22:33,393
Jung-yun really gave it his all today.

487
00:22:33,477 --> 00:22:34,561
He really did.

488
00:22:35,604 --> 00:22:38,482
When she said we'd talk more later,

489
00:22:38,565 --> 00:22:41,360
all I did was wait for that moment.

490
00:22:43,362 --> 00:22:44,363
Oh!

491
00:22:45,697 --> 00:22:47,741
- Whose is this?
- Oh, sorry.

492
00:22:48,367 --> 00:22:49,451
Yeah, it's yours.

493
00:22:49,534 --> 00:22:51,995
- I'm guess I'm off.
- Is this right? Hold on.

494
00:22:52,079 --> 00:22:53,330
Bye.

495
00:22:57,292 --> 00:23:01,463
I think I tried to act
nonchalant in front of the others,

496
00:23:02,047 --> 00:23:03,882
like I didn't really care,

497
00:23:03,965 --> 00:23:05,467
but the truth is,

498
00:23:07,094 --> 00:23:09,012
I don't think I can help…

499
00:23:10,389 --> 00:23:11,932
feeling disappointed.

500
00:23:12,641 --> 00:23:15,102
I honestly don't think

501
00:23:15,185 --> 00:23:18,688
I'll have the courage
to ask her to talk again.

502
00:23:22,275 --> 00:23:25,153
I've confessed my feelings for someone

503
00:23:25,237 --> 00:23:27,614
three times in my life,

504
00:23:27,697 --> 00:23:29,950
and with each failure, my confidence…

505
00:23:31,034 --> 00:23:32,619
continues to decrease.

506
00:23:33,537 --> 00:23:35,747
I had no confidence,

507
00:23:35,831 --> 00:23:38,083
and there was this very real fear that

508
00:23:38,166 --> 00:23:40,544
I would never be able
to have a relationship.

509
00:23:42,421 --> 00:23:43,839
In the end,

510
00:23:44,589 --> 00:23:46,550
I told myself to just…

511
00:23:48,301 --> 00:23:51,388
give up any hope
of having a romantic relationship.

512
00:23:54,099 --> 00:23:56,601
And then one day I realized

513
00:23:56,685 --> 00:23:59,146
that my hope was gradually declining.

514
00:24:01,857 --> 00:24:06,570
And that was the whole reason
that I decided to come on the show.

515
00:24:07,154 --> 00:24:08,613
Because I wanted to change.

516
00:24:08,697 --> 00:24:11,658
So I knew I had to muster up the courage.

517
00:24:15,912 --> 00:24:16,997
Mmm.

518
00:24:18,999 --> 00:24:21,501
I just want to open up my heart, but…

519
00:24:24,296 --> 00:24:25,422
I don't know.

520
00:24:46,026 --> 00:24:47,152
I don't think…

521
00:24:48,862 --> 00:24:52,449
that it's really truly over yet.

522
00:24:53,658 --> 00:24:54,659
But…

523
00:24:56,828 --> 00:24:59,581
I can't really help…

524
00:25:03,001 --> 00:25:04,002
…well…

525
00:25:05,795 --> 00:25:08,131
feeling like it is, like it's over.

526
00:25:11,760 --> 00:25:12,761
Yeah.

527
00:25:21,394 --> 00:25:22,395
God.

528
00:25:29,194 --> 00:25:30,028
Oh.

529
00:25:31,863 --> 00:25:34,491
- He's really hurt. Hurt and disappointed.
- He really is.

530
00:25:35,325 --> 00:25:37,577
Looks like he's really heartbroken.

531
00:25:37,661 --> 00:25:40,497
Gosh, the sound of him crying,
and he's trying to hold in his sadness.

532
00:25:40,580 --> 00:25:41,414
Yeah.

533
00:25:41,498 --> 00:25:44,167
Right now, Jung-yun is very devastated.

534
00:25:44,251 --> 00:25:47,128
Even breathing is difficult.
You know that feeling, right?

535
00:25:47,212 --> 00:25:50,215
It's like you have a fever,
and your chest burns.

536
00:25:50,298 --> 00:25:54,219
I found it really sad when he said,
"I told myself to give up any hope."

537
00:25:54,302 --> 00:25:55,303
Yeah.

538
00:25:55,387 --> 00:25:58,139
Because when someone
keeps having bad experiences,

539
00:25:58,223 --> 00:26:01,226
they give up hope because
there's been too much disappointment.

540
00:26:01,309 --> 00:26:03,311
It's to avoid getting hurt again.

541
00:26:03,395 --> 00:26:05,772
"Would you ask to see me?"
"Would you write to me?"

542
00:26:05,855 --> 00:26:08,108
"Would you give me a gift?"
All those things, I can now see--

543
00:26:08,191 --> 00:26:09,484
There was a reason for it.

544
00:26:09,568 --> 00:26:12,028
He's been rejected so many times
that he's become cautious.

545
00:26:12,112 --> 00:26:14,155
I was so frustrated with him,
but I feel bad now.

546
00:26:14,239 --> 00:26:15,282
That's what it was.

547
00:26:15,365 --> 00:26:17,242
I only hope he doesn't get
too hung up on it.

548
00:26:17,325 --> 00:26:20,036
I hope he cries it out today
and then brushes it off tomorrow.

549
00:26:20,120 --> 00:26:23,415
NORAEBANG

550
00:26:24,374 --> 00:26:26,918
I guess those guys
are having a great time right now.

551
00:26:27,002 --> 00:26:29,045
Oh, she's the one I like the most.

552
00:26:29,129 --> 00:26:31,256
Yeah, I'm really worried about Hyun-seo.

553
00:26:31,339 --> 00:26:34,426
Why? He was pretty firm.

554
00:26:34,509 --> 00:26:37,137
I really tried hard
to make my feelings obvious.

555
00:26:37,220 --> 00:26:38,972
- To make them obvious?
- Yeah. Uh-huh.

556
00:26:39,055 --> 00:26:41,099
I'm really bad at showing my feelings,

557
00:26:41,182 --> 00:26:44,603
but I really went out of my way to make it
obvious, in case he couldn't notice.

558
00:26:44,686 --> 00:26:46,563
You were successful. It was pretty clear.

559
00:26:46,646 --> 00:26:49,232
- It was really obvious.
- Hyun-seo did make it obvious.

560
00:26:49,316 --> 00:26:52,819
- And the whole thing with the tumbler…
- But we don't know who it was from.

561
00:26:52,902 --> 00:26:55,322
Hey, who are you trying to fool right now?

562
00:26:55,405 --> 00:26:57,407
That was a seal. That was a seal.

563
00:26:57,490 --> 00:27:00,160
- Exactly. They were basically a done deal.
- Yeah.

564
00:27:00,243 --> 00:27:03,246
But that's precisely
what I'm worried about right now.

565
00:27:03,330 --> 00:27:05,790
So far, the dates have been random,

566
00:27:05,874 --> 00:27:08,084
and all of my dates were with Hyuk-joon,

567
00:27:08,168 --> 00:27:11,755
so I never had a chance
to talk to anyone else.

568
00:27:11,838 --> 00:27:15,383
So I don't even know who to pick
for a second choice.

569
00:27:17,552 --> 00:27:19,387
Are you being weeded out?

570
00:27:19,471 --> 00:27:20,472
Yeah.

571
00:27:21,431 --> 00:27:23,475
- Tae-hoon.
- Don't provoke her.

572
00:27:23,558 --> 00:27:24,893
- This is not the time.
- Exactly.

573
00:27:25,769 --> 00:27:28,313
If I get another chance to go on a date,

574
00:27:29,147 --> 00:27:30,482
I'm totally…

575
00:27:30,565 --> 00:27:31,733
Choosing someone else?

576
00:27:32,317 --> 00:27:35,403
But I swear, if I get Hyuk-joon again,

577
00:27:35,487 --> 00:27:38,323
I think it'll be really hard for me.

578
00:27:41,701 --> 00:27:43,203
Who could this be now?

579
00:27:59,594 --> 00:28:03,431
Despite coming here
with already low expectations,

580
00:28:04,349 --> 00:28:08,395
I kept on running into situations
that were even worse than I expected,

581
00:28:08,478 --> 00:28:09,813
so it's been tough.

582
00:28:11,106 --> 00:28:14,901
I had fun on my date with Jin-woo, but…

583
00:28:15,527 --> 00:28:17,445
You should call me boss lady from now on.

584
00:28:17,529 --> 00:28:19,572
Boss lady?

585
00:28:20,407 --> 00:28:24,035
Uh-huh. I like hearing someone
call me boss lady.

586
00:28:24,119 --> 00:28:25,036
AFTER THE DATE ON DAY 3

587
00:28:25,120 --> 00:28:26,162
- Did you have fun?
- I did.

588
00:28:26,246 --> 00:28:28,998
I practically shoved my confession
of love down his throat.

589
00:28:29,082 --> 00:28:30,542
- Oh, you did?
- Yeah.

590
00:28:30,625 --> 00:28:32,961
I was like, "I like your face.
You look like Lai Kuan-lin."

591
00:28:33,044 --> 00:28:34,963
You told him he looks like Lai Kuan-lin?

592
00:28:36,673 --> 00:28:37,674
So…

593
00:28:37,757 --> 00:28:40,677
Han-ju was really aggressive, wasn't she?
Oh, dear.

594
00:28:40,760 --> 00:28:44,305
Han-ju, yeah, she really liked Jin-woo.
He is her first choice.

595
00:28:44,389 --> 00:28:46,725
The most memorable person
for me is Jin-woo,

596
00:28:46,808 --> 00:28:48,601
who joined partway through.

597
00:28:48,685 --> 00:28:50,353
I wanted to go on a date with Jin-woo.

598
00:28:50,437 --> 00:28:52,355
I'm interested in Jin-woo,

599
00:28:52,439 --> 00:28:54,858
so I was really happy to go
on a date with him.

600
00:28:55,734 --> 00:28:57,527
My current first choice is Jin-woo.

601
00:29:02,574 --> 00:29:06,494
She found out for sure what his
feelings were at the 5 Minute Library.

602
00:29:06,578 --> 00:29:09,289
BEST ROTATION DATE CONVERSATION?
HAN SU-JI

603
00:29:11,791 --> 00:29:14,669
It wasn't so much
about what was in the diary.

604
00:29:14,753 --> 00:29:17,464
It was more the fact that I'd hoped
my first choice

605
00:29:17,547 --> 00:29:19,549
would be to pick me for the date.

606
00:29:43,198 --> 00:29:46,826
I always thought the reason
I was failing at dating

607
00:29:46,910 --> 00:29:50,872
was because I hadn't gone all-out
in my efforts,

608
00:29:50,955 --> 00:29:55,293
so the fact that I was
putting in all this effort,

609
00:29:56,377 --> 00:29:58,797
and it still isn't working out,

610
00:29:58,880 --> 00:30:01,341
is really affecting my self-esteem.

611
00:30:04,427 --> 00:30:07,639
Until now,
I haven't really attempted to date

612
00:30:08,640 --> 00:30:10,642
out of fear of rejection,

613
00:30:10,725 --> 00:30:14,145
so this is the first time
I've been hurt by rejection.

614
00:30:20,568 --> 00:30:22,612
Yeah, so it's not "I didn't date,"

615
00:30:23,363 --> 00:30:24,989
it's that I couldn't date.

616
00:30:30,495 --> 00:30:34,082
All my life,
I thought I was a decent person.

617
00:30:35,041 --> 00:30:39,337
But now I think, "Ah, I guess
I really do have a lot of shortcomings."

618
00:30:42,173 --> 00:30:46,177
You know how they say,
"Kids aren't afraid of fire or cars"?

619
00:30:47,220 --> 00:30:51,140
Because they don't know these things
can cause pain and should be feared.

620
00:30:51,224 --> 00:30:54,936
I should've dated when I was young
so I could've…

621
00:30:56,479 --> 00:30:58,731
experienced hurt early on,

622
00:30:58,815 --> 00:31:01,401
and could have built up a tolerance.

623
00:31:02,193 --> 00:31:04,279
Experiencing this as an adult…

624
00:31:07,699 --> 00:31:09,284
it's a lot to deal with.

625
00:31:11,828 --> 00:31:14,372
It feels like I'm attempting
to do something

626
00:31:14,455 --> 00:31:17,083
everyone else has built immunity to.

627
00:31:17,166 --> 00:31:18,877
It's just really difficult.

628
00:31:22,839 --> 00:31:25,675
Of course it's upsetting.

629
00:31:25,758 --> 00:31:28,553
- Yeah, this must be very disheartening.
- Oh, dear.

630
00:31:33,182 --> 00:31:34,392
How are you, Mom?

631
00:31:34,475 --> 00:31:36,436
- She's called her mom.
- She's calling home.

632
00:31:36,519 --> 00:31:39,063
No, no one's interested in me here.

633
00:31:43,735 --> 00:31:46,321
I feel like I'm not good enough.

634
00:31:58,333 --> 00:32:02,462
If everyone here were
on the same level as me,

635
00:32:02,545 --> 00:32:05,757
like, if we were all comparable,

636
00:32:07,592 --> 00:32:09,218
then I would just think,

637
00:32:09,302 --> 00:32:12,180
"Oh, well, we're not compatible."

638
00:32:12,263 --> 00:32:17,810
But all the other girls here
are, like, so pretty.

639
00:32:17,894 --> 00:32:20,313
It's completely killed my self-esteem.

640
00:32:32,700 --> 00:32:33,993
Oh, Han-ju…

641
00:32:35,745 --> 00:32:37,538
Today is full of heartbreaks.

642
00:32:38,539 --> 00:32:41,167
Of course she's crushed.
She only liked one guy.

643
00:32:41,250 --> 00:32:43,503
It's a huge hit to the psyche
when you like someone that much.

644
00:32:43,586 --> 00:32:44,879
That's right. It's true.

645
00:32:44,963 --> 00:32:47,674
But while their hearts might be
in turmoil right now,

646
00:32:47,757 --> 00:32:52,011
they really need to realize that
no one has been rejected for sure yet.

647
00:32:52,095 --> 00:32:54,597
- Oh, good point. That's so true.
- Yeah, that's right.

648
00:32:54,681 --> 00:32:57,684
- That's so true.
- One strikeout isn't the end of the game.

649
00:32:57,767 --> 00:32:59,477
Yes, you're totally right.

650
00:32:59,560 --> 00:33:02,647
Honestly, what breaks my heart is that
they keep blaming themselves

651
00:33:02,730 --> 00:33:04,273
and letting it affect their self-esteem.

652
00:33:04,357 --> 00:33:05,566
"I'm not good enough."

653
00:33:05,650 --> 00:33:08,653
They feel ashamed for putting themselves
out there, and they really shouldn't.

654
00:33:08,736 --> 00:33:09,946
KIM SOO-HYUN
JEON SEO-YOON

655
00:33:10,029 --> 00:33:12,156
Ugh, I need to talk to Tae-hoon.

656
00:33:12,240 --> 00:33:14,826
- Should I go knock on his door?
- Ask him to come out.

657
00:33:14,909 --> 00:33:16,661
Is that too much? Should I not go?

658
00:33:16,744 --> 00:33:19,163
- No, go! Just go.
- I want to, but I'm too nervous.

659
00:33:19,247 --> 00:33:20,415
Do it, Soo-hyun. Go!

660
00:33:20,498 --> 00:33:22,083
No, I've never done this before.

661
00:33:22,166 --> 00:33:24,168
The only door I've ever knocked on
is my dad's.

662
00:33:24,252 --> 00:33:26,504
The only room I'm in and out of
all day is my parents'.

663
00:33:26,587 --> 00:33:28,840
Oh, it's your first time going
to a guy's room?

664
00:33:28,923 --> 00:33:30,800
- Want me to go with you?
- No, Seo-yoon, it's fine.

665
00:33:30,883 --> 00:33:32,135
No, she has to go alone.

666
00:33:32,218 --> 00:33:35,680
No, I'll go alone.
I've been to my brother's room.

667
00:33:36,264 --> 00:33:37,473
That's a guy's room.

668
00:33:37,557 --> 00:33:39,600
That's true. Don't be nervous.

669
00:33:39,684 --> 00:33:42,311
You've got this.
Do you know what you'll say

670
00:33:43,521 --> 00:33:45,314
if Tae-hoon comes to the door?

671
00:33:45,398 --> 00:33:47,025
I'll say, "Can we talk for a second?"

672
00:33:47,108 --> 00:33:49,819
- And if Jin-woo comes to the door?
- "Could you grab Tae-hoon for me?"

673
00:33:49,902 --> 00:33:52,447
Okay. So Tae-hoon comes out.
What do you say?

674
00:33:52,530 --> 00:33:55,158
- "I have something to ask you."
- "What is it?"

675
00:33:55,241 --> 00:33:57,827
"I just finished the blueberry smoothie.
It was delicious."

676
00:33:57,910 --> 00:33:59,954
"I look forward
to a strawberry one tomorrow."

677
00:34:00,038 --> 00:34:01,664
Good. Now, go.

678
00:34:01,748 --> 00:34:04,167
- Look at them rehearsing.
- So cute.

679
00:34:04,250 --> 00:34:06,335
Oh, man, I can't take this.

680
00:34:06,419 --> 00:34:09,088
- She's beaming.
- Aw, she is so cute.

681
00:34:09,172 --> 00:34:10,339
She's too cute.

682
00:34:10,423 --> 00:34:13,092
- They're the blueberry couple.
- This couple makes my heart flutter.

683
00:34:14,469 --> 00:34:15,553
Here it is.

684
00:34:17,805 --> 00:34:19,223
LEE JIN-WOO
KIM TAE-HOON

685
00:34:21,142 --> 00:34:22,769
Are they going to answer?

686
00:34:23,686 --> 00:34:25,229
Is Tae-hoon in there, by any chance?

687
00:34:25,313 --> 00:34:26,939
- He's not.
- No? Oh, are you alone?

688
00:34:27,023 --> 00:34:28,483
Yeah. I think he's in the lounge.

689
00:34:32,862 --> 00:34:34,238
Where is he?

690
00:34:35,823 --> 00:34:37,700
Where could he be?

691
00:34:37,784 --> 00:34:40,745
Come on, come on. Where could he be?

692
00:34:41,329 --> 00:34:43,414
What's going on here?
Some kind of boy talk?

693
00:34:43,498 --> 00:34:45,875
- I'll give her another gift.
- Oh, they look so serious.

694
00:34:45,958 --> 00:34:48,086
Oh, the atmosphere is too serious.

695
00:34:49,545 --> 00:34:52,090
So I was trying to avoid getting hurt…

696
00:34:53,758 --> 00:34:55,760
Is this a serious conversation?

697
00:34:55,843 --> 00:34:58,054
- No, we're done.
- Oh, yeah?

698
00:34:58,137 --> 00:35:00,056
- Yeah, you can join us. We don't mind.
- You sure?

699
00:35:00,139 --> 00:35:01,307
- Yeah.
- It's all right?

700
00:35:01,390 --> 00:35:03,893
- Who are you here to see?
- I wanted to talk to you.

701
00:35:03,976 --> 00:35:05,812
- That's it, go on.
- That's it.

702
00:35:05,895 --> 00:35:08,231
- Why? Where to?
- Shall we go over there?

703
00:35:08,314 --> 00:35:09,857
- It's cold outside.
- Okay.

704
00:35:11,901 --> 00:35:13,444
What's with the mood in there?

705
00:35:13,528 --> 00:35:15,613
Oh, did you pick up on that? I mean, we…

706
00:35:15,696 --> 00:35:17,281
I was pretty shocked about it too.

707
00:35:19,617 --> 00:35:23,037
So do you guys all know each
of your first and second choices?

708
00:35:23,121 --> 00:35:24,247
Pretty much.

709
00:35:25,373 --> 00:35:26,666
We're all aware, you know?

710
00:35:26,749 --> 00:35:29,836
So, have you made a firm decision?

711
00:35:31,295 --> 00:35:32,839
- Really?
- Yeah.

712
00:35:32,922 --> 00:35:34,674
- No way.
- Are you…

713
00:35:35,383 --> 00:35:36,634
- "Soo-hyun"?
- "Are you"?

714
00:35:36,717 --> 00:35:38,845
- Come on, say it again!
- Wait, what did he say?

715
00:35:38,928 --> 00:35:41,973
- Wow! What are you waiting for?
- A segment within a segment.

716
00:35:42,056 --> 00:35:44,183
- Oh, my God!
- Tae-hoon and Soo-hyun.

717
00:35:44,267 --> 00:35:45,643
Blueberry smoothie.

718
00:35:45,726 --> 00:35:47,019
Are you…

719
00:35:47,687 --> 00:35:48,896
Are you what?

720
00:35:51,149 --> 00:35:53,943
- They're both frozen.
- I think I've decided.

721
00:35:55,653 --> 00:35:56,904
Yeah?

722
00:35:58,656 --> 00:36:00,533
I made a choice and focused on it.

723
00:36:00,616 --> 00:36:02,285
- You're done?
- So, yeah, I'm done.

724
00:36:02,368 --> 00:36:04,662
Hmm. I see.

725
00:36:04,745 --> 00:36:06,664
Soo-hyun, don't you realize?

726
00:36:07,456 --> 00:36:10,334
I was really nervous,
sitting there thinking,

727
00:36:10,418 --> 00:36:12,044
"Oh, could that be me?"

728
00:36:12,128 --> 00:36:14,172
This couple's giving me
serious heart flutters.

729
00:36:14,255 --> 00:36:16,257
Tell me about the new release.

730
00:36:16,966 --> 00:36:18,050
Tell you what?

731
00:36:18,134 --> 00:36:20,595
I've been dying to know
what's in the new release.

732
00:36:20,678 --> 00:36:22,388
Is it from yesterday's confessionals?

733
00:36:22,471 --> 00:36:24,682
Well, let's just say
it's from recent ones.

734
00:36:24,765 --> 00:36:27,393
- I don't wanna spoil it for you.
- Come on!

735
00:36:27,476 --> 00:36:29,645
Well, you should've tried harder,
don't you think?

736
00:36:29,729 --> 00:36:31,856
Hey, I was the first or maybe second
to get there.

737
00:36:31,939 --> 00:36:34,400
All I had to do was go to my room
and grab the coupons.

738
00:36:34,483 --> 00:36:35,860
But I suddenly had this doubt…

739
00:36:35,943 --> 00:36:38,321
That you were going too far?
Now is the time to spend!

740
00:36:38,404 --> 00:36:39,655
Get more for your money.

741
00:36:41,282 --> 00:36:44,035
- That's not true.
- Sure, it is. It absolutely is.

742
00:36:44,118 --> 00:36:46,579
- That's not true. Don't say that.
- But, you know…

743
00:36:46,662 --> 00:36:49,123
- Or I'm going to regret this.
- Come on, say it. Tell her.

744
00:36:49,207 --> 00:36:51,709
He needs to tell her
that he spent two coupons to read…

745
00:36:51,792 --> 00:36:54,003
- Did you read them consecutively?
- Huh?

746
00:36:54,086 --> 00:36:58,007
When you were in there, did you read the
same person's diaries one after the other?

747
00:36:58,090 --> 00:36:59,884
- No, I didn't read that person's.
- Really?

748
00:36:59,967 --> 00:37:01,093
Yep.

749
00:37:01,177 --> 00:37:04,138
Just tell her. Tell her you spent
two coupons to read hers.

750
00:37:04,222 --> 00:37:06,390
- Yeah, come on.
- Why isn't he telling her?

751
00:37:06,474 --> 00:37:10,102
What could this be? You're not going
to tell me whose you read, are you?

752
00:37:10,686 --> 00:37:13,189
Hmm. When should I tell you?

753
00:37:13,272 --> 00:37:14,357
Is he shy?

754
00:37:14,440 --> 00:37:17,860
"When should I tell you?"
Ugh, what is this? I can't take it.

755
00:37:19,195 --> 00:37:22,031
Ugh, I thought I'd get you
to tell me, but you're not falling for it.

756
00:37:22,114 --> 00:37:24,825
I only came here because
I thought I could get it out of you.

757
00:37:24,909 --> 00:37:27,078
That might've happened yesterday
while we were drinking,

758
00:37:27,161 --> 00:37:29,247
but I think you missed your chance.

759
00:37:29,330 --> 00:37:30,248
Man…

760
00:37:30,331 --> 00:37:33,292
I can't tell you how happy
I was that I checked hers out.

761
00:37:33,376 --> 00:37:35,044
Yep, two coupons. Totally worth it.

762
00:37:35,544 --> 00:37:38,506
I did kind of think he could've read mine,

763
00:37:38,589 --> 00:37:40,132
but I wasn't sure.

764
00:37:40,216 --> 00:37:41,884
Can't you tell me?

765
00:37:41,968 --> 00:37:44,178
Because he wouldn't tell me when I asked.

766
00:37:44,262 --> 00:37:46,806
- Aw, what is this?
- Oh, it just hit me.

767
00:37:46,889 --> 00:37:48,307
- What? What is it?
- What has?

768
00:37:48,391 --> 00:37:50,434
If he hesitates to this extent
without telling her…

769
00:37:50,518 --> 00:37:52,478
- That means yes.
- Right. Right.

770
00:37:52,561 --> 00:37:54,146
- Get the hint.
- "I think it's me."

771
00:37:54,230 --> 00:37:55,273
She's gonna get the hint.

772
00:37:55,356 --> 00:37:57,233
Because if it weren't her,
he'd tell her who it is.

773
00:37:57,316 --> 00:37:59,193
Are we seeing Tae-hoon
playing hard to get?

774
00:37:59,277 --> 00:38:01,946
I think this is just how
these two engage with each other.

775
00:38:02,029 --> 00:38:03,572
Oh, this is their banter.

776
00:38:03,656 --> 00:38:08,119
And by doing this, they're just
elongating this date and conversation.

777
00:38:08,202 --> 00:38:10,788
Aw, these two know how to be romantic.

778
00:38:11,372 --> 00:38:12,832
How'd it go with Jae-seo?

779
00:38:14,792 --> 00:38:16,168
I think it's too soon for this.

780
00:38:16,252 --> 00:38:19,588
I can't remember if
you were there when I said this earlier,

781
00:38:19,672 --> 00:38:23,426
but Jae-seo said to me,
"I might be your last date today."

782
00:38:23,509 --> 00:38:25,720
This one might be
the last one for you today.

783
00:38:25,803 --> 00:38:28,806
- Yes, this affected her a lot.
- Jae-seo? He said that?

784
00:38:28,889 --> 00:38:31,851
He's such a blabbermouth. He's always
saying things that are uncalled for.

785
00:38:31,934 --> 00:38:36,063
So he was like, "When it's the three
of us, let's just have fun,

786
00:38:36,147 --> 00:38:39,942
and I'd like to talk about the other stuff
when it's just you and me."

787
00:38:40,026 --> 00:38:42,320
- How did you respond?
- He really needs to be kept in check.

788
00:38:42,403 --> 00:38:43,279
It was out of nowhere.

789
00:38:43,362 --> 00:38:45,156
When he needs to be kept in check,
teach him a lesson.

790
00:38:45,239 --> 00:38:47,658
- Oh, no!
- Why is he sauntering? Ugh!

791
00:38:49,368 --> 00:38:51,078
Yes?

792
00:38:56,083 --> 00:38:58,002
- Oh! Hi.
- Hey, are you two together?

793
00:38:58,085 --> 00:38:59,754
- Do you want to talk to--
- Is she sleeping?

794
00:38:59,837 --> 00:39:01,839
- No. Want me to get her?
- Oh, no.

795
00:39:01,922 --> 00:39:02,965
"Oh, no, no."

796
00:39:03,049 --> 00:39:05,509
Oh, hearing his voice made her stop short.

797
00:39:05,593 --> 00:39:07,720
- I'll wait for you. We'll go together.
- Okay.

798
00:39:20,274 --> 00:39:21,776
- Who was it?
- That was Jae-seo.

799
00:39:21,859 --> 00:39:23,110
- Just him?
- Yeah.

800
00:39:23,194 --> 00:39:25,237
Oh, really?
I thought there were two of them.

801
00:39:25,321 --> 00:39:28,324
No, no. I get the feeling
he wanted to talk to you.

802
00:39:30,701 --> 00:39:31,786
Let's go.

803
00:39:35,122 --> 00:39:36,165
- Hello.
- Hello.

804
00:39:36,248 --> 00:39:39,210
- Can I have three minutes of your time?
- Oh, sure, yeah, of course.

805
00:39:39,293 --> 00:39:42,380
I hope Jae-seo doesn't stick
his foot in his mouth again.

806
00:39:42,463 --> 00:39:45,132
- Tell me about it.
- Please don't. Ugh, please don't.

807
00:39:45,758 --> 00:39:48,511
So, did you…
not go on any more dates today?

808
00:39:48,594 --> 00:39:50,054
- What do you mean?
- After our date.

809
00:39:50,137 --> 00:39:51,555
No, just like you predicted, isn't it?

810
00:39:51,639 --> 00:39:54,433
- Geez, why would he…
- There's no need to remind her.

811
00:39:54,517 --> 00:39:55,893
Oh, well,

812
00:39:56,977 --> 00:39:59,355
I just thought you should understand
what's been going on.

813
00:39:59,438 --> 00:40:00,940
- Oh.
- Yeah.

814
00:40:02,650 --> 00:40:06,028
Um, at first I thought
there wouldn't be any interest.

815
00:40:06,112 --> 00:40:08,781
- Oh, you thought there wouldn't be?
- In either direction.

816
00:40:08,864 --> 00:40:11,117
I thought no one would be
interested in me,

817
00:40:11,200 --> 00:40:13,411
and I thought I wouldn't be interested
in anyone.

818
00:40:14,495 --> 00:40:16,956
But then,
you were the second person to arrive.

819
00:40:23,170 --> 00:40:24,547
Oh, hello.

820
00:40:25,923 --> 00:40:27,091
Oh, hello.

821
00:40:27,174 --> 00:40:28,259
Hello.

822
00:40:29,009 --> 00:40:30,678
When you first opened the door,

823
00:40:31,303 --> 00:40:33,556
I thought something must be wrong.

824
00:40:33,639 --> 00:40:36,308
- It was like that right from the start.
- Oh.

825
00:40:36,392 --> 00:40:39,353
You see, for my ideal type, I'd put,

826
00:40:39,437 --> 00:40:41,397
"Someone like Park Bo-young."

827
00:40:42,022 --> 00:40:43,441
That's nothing like me, is it?

828
00:40:43,524 --> 00:40:45,317
- You--
- Are you trying to destroy me?

829
00:40:45,401 --> 00:40:48,195
No, not at all. Am I being too blunt?

830
00:40:48,279 --> 00:40:51,740
Anyway, that's how it was right
from my first impression of you.

831
00:40:51,824 --> 00:40:53,284
- Oh, really?
- Yeah.

832
00:40:53,367 --> 00:40:56,662
I tend to go for that kind of…

833
00:40:56,745 --> 00:40:59,248
you know, like, cute and playful type.

834
00:40:59,331 --> 00:41:02,501
Gosh, he's confessing
his feelings very slowly.

835
00:41:02,585 --> 00:41:06,464
So I've been wanting to talk one-on-one
so I could get that off my chest,

836
00:41:06,547 --> 00:41:07,882
but the timing hasn't been right.

837
00:41:07,965 --> 00:41:08,841
Yeah, I understand.

838
00:41:08,924 --> 00:41:11,385
And I didn't want to stress you out
more than you already were.

839
00:41:11,469 --> 00:41:13,304
- Mmm.
- So, that's what happened.

840
00:41:14,472 --> 00:41:17,349
And then I was just like,
"When would I tell her if not now?"

841
00:41:17,433 --> 00:41:18,726
- Oh, totally.
- That kind of thing.

842
00:41:18,809 --> 00:41:20,853
Jae-seo's doing a good job right now.

843
00:41:20,936 --> 00:41:24,315
And actually, when we were arm wrestling,
and you were in fifth place…

844
00:41:24,398 --> 00:41:25,608
Oh, right.

845
00:41:25,691 --> 00:41:27,902
5TH PLACE
ARM WRESTLING COMPETITION

846
00:41:27,985 --> 00:41:29,862
…I realized, "Oh, I can throw this match

847
00:41:29,945 --> 00:41:31,572
and won't have to reveal who I like."

848
00:41:32,072 --> 00:41:33,157
Whoa, hey!

849
00:41:34,492 --> 00:41:36,410
Hold on! Man, I am no match for you.

850
00:41:36,494 --> 00:41:40,664
You see, I thought I should let you know
how things actually went down,

851
00:41:40,748 --> 00:41:41,874
to put your mind at ease.

852
00:41:41,957 --> 00:41:44,001
- Oh, thank you. You're right.
- Yeah, sure.

853
00:41:44,084 --> 00:41:46,045
I think I needed to hear that.

854
00:41:46,128 --> 00:41:50,633
Oh, he's thinking, "I'll tell you my story
so that you're not taken by surprise."

855
00:41:52,510 --> 00:41:56,305
So going forward, if there's
an opportunity for me to choose someone,

856
00:41:56,388 --> 00:41:58,057
there's a high chance I'll choose you.

857
00:41:58,140 --> 00:41:59,266
Mmm.

858
00:42:00,893 --> 00:42:04,480
- I don't want to catch you off guard.
- Yeah, I get it. I won't be surprised.

859
00:42:04,563 --> 00:42:06,690
Advance notice. That's nice.

860
00:42:06,774 --> 00:42:08,984
I'm the type of person
who needs a heads-up.

861
00:42:09,068 --> 00:42:12,154
Yeah, Jae-seo thinks telling her like this
is being considerate.

862
00:42:12,238 --> 00:42:13,864
- Right.
- "Don't be surprised."

863
00:42:19,203 --> 00:42:20,913
That's all I wanted to say today.

864
00:42:20,996 --> 00:42:22,373
Got it. Okay.

865
00:42:23,165 --> 00:42:25,292
Anyway, it was really nice
talking with you.

866
00:42:25,376 --> 00:42:26,794
- Yeah, for sure.
- Let's go.

867
00:42:26,877 --> 00:42:28,379
Let's go.

868
00:42:28,462 --> 00:42:29,797
Back into the cold.

869
00:42:30,297 --> 00:42:32,633
Man, this weather's insane.
It's going to start raining tomorrow.

870
00:42:32,716 --> 00:42:34,426
- Oh, it's going to rain tomorrow?
- Yeah.

871
00:42:34,510 --> 00:42:36,845
- I want to stay inside, then.
- I know, right?

872
00:42:38,347 --> 00:42:41,600
I think today
I've at least expressed my feelings.

873
00:42:41,684 --> 00:42:43,852
I think I've explained to her

874
00:42:43,936 --> 00:42:47,064
in a way that she could understand
that I have feelings for her.

875
00:42:50,484 --> 00:42:53,028
I feel like the weight's been lifted
off my shoulders.

876
00:42:57,324 --> 00:42:59,076
If I'm being totally honest,

877
00:42:59,785 --> 00:43:02,997
even though Jae-seo expressed
his feelings for me…

878
00:43:03,080 --> 00:43:06,333
I mean, of course I was grateful
for what he said,

879
00:43:06,417 --> 00:43:11,088
but I didn't get butterflies in my stomach
or anything like that.

880
00:43:11,755 --> 00:43:14,466
My only thoughts about it were,

881
00:43:14,550 --> 00:43:19,179
"I really appreciate your feelings,
but I don't think I can reciprocate them."

882
00:43:21,056 --> 00:43:24,184
If she had feelings for him,
that would've given her butterflies.

883
00:43:24,268 --> 00:43:27,521
It was like he was explaining everything
very systematically and logically.

884
00:43:27,605 --> 00:43:28,480
Right.

885
00:43:28,564 --> 00:43:31,358
But it wasn't something that would
move you or touch your heart.

886
00:43:31,442 --> 00:43:33,027
It didn't have the emotional impact of,

887
00:43:33,110 --> 00:43:35,112
"Oh, my God,
I can't believe that's how he's feeling."

888
00:43:35,195 --> 00:43:37,698
No, it doesn't. It's more like
he's briefing her on the situation.

889
00:43:37,781 --> 00:43:39,658
- I thought that was a shame.
- That's right.

890
00:43:39,742 --> 00:43:42,077
But even that must've taken a huge
amount of courage on his part.

891
00:43:42,161 --> 00:43:42,995
Yeah, truly.

892
00:43:43,871 --> 00:43:45,956
This feels like unrequited love.

893
00:43:46,040 --> 00:43:49,001
I'm so jealous that the three of them
are in there by themselves.

894
00:43:53,047 --> 00:43:56,842
I think the reason I keep feeling down has
something to do with my makeover.

895
00:43:58,344 --> 00:44:00,846
I want to tell you, but I can't.
Just forget it.

896
00:44:00,929 --> 00:44:02,514
I don't mind telling you about mine.

897
00:44:02,598 --> 00:44:04,350
Me neither. Mine really wasn't a big deal.

898
00:44:04,433 --> 00:44:05,893
Mine wasn't a big deal either.

899
00:44:06,518 --> 00:44:07,686
I had psychotherapy.

900
00:44:07,770 --> 00:44:09,271
- Oh, really?
- Oh.

901
00:44:11,690 --> 00:44:15,235
Because I've never been confident.

902
00:44:18,155 --> 00:44:20,824
No one I've ever liked
has ever liked me back.

903
00:44:21,659 --> 00:44:25,329
So whenever I have a crush on someone,
I tried to get rid of those feelings.

904
00:44:25,412 --> 00:44:27,247
I never tried to approach anyone.

905
00:44:29,500 --> 00:44:33,629
And my parents just made things worse,
so I never opened up to anyone.

906
00:44:34,380 --> 00:44:38,550
I always felt that expecting anything
from anyone would just get me hurt.

907
00:44:40,135 --> 00:44:41,887
I have an older brother who,

908
00:44:41,970 --> 00:44:44,640
when we were growing up,
was good at everything.

909
00:44:44,723 --> 00:44:48,894
He was a good speaker, he always
managed whatever was on his plate,

910
00:44:48,977 --> 00:44:52,648
he got good grades,
and he was also popular.

911
00:44:52,731 --> 00:44:57,861
So my parents were never satisfied
with my accomplishments.

912
00:44:58,696 --> 00:45:01,865
Always telling me to do better,
like my brother.

913
00:45:02,616 --> 00:45:04,910
Whenever I got cranky

914
00:45:04,993 --> 00:45:07,788
or complained due to stresses in my life…

915
00:45:07,871 --> 00:45:08,706
I see.

916
00:45:08,789 --> 00:45:09,998
…my parents would be like,

917
00:45:10,082 --> 00:45:13,377
"Oh, I thought you were a good kid,
not like the others.

918
00:45:13,460 --> 00:45:16,338
But I guess you're just the same
after all."

919
00:45:17,464 --> 00:45:21,176
Hearing all of that constantly
ingrained in me

920
00:45:21,844 --> 00:45:25,806
this idea that
I should never make mistakes

921
00:45:25,889 --> 00:45:29,893
and should always show only my best side
when interacting with others.

922
00:45:31,520 --> 00:45:34,606
That's why In-guk told me not to give up

923
00:45:34,690 --> 00:45:37,609
and to focus on my feelings
and just go for it,

924
00:45:38,318 --> 00:45:39,862
no matter what others do.

925
00:45:41,655 --> 00:45:45,492
But now that I'm back in a situation where
my feelings aren't being reciprocated,

926
00:45:45,576 --> 00:45:48,954
I keep comparing myself to her,
which is getting me down again.

927
00:45:49,663 --> 00:45:52,750
I came here to get away from that,
and I thought things were going okay,

928
00:45:53,417 --> 00:45:56,086
but being back in a situation
that's so emotionally taxing

929
00:45:56,170 --> 00:45:57,629
just makes me want to run away.

930
00:45:58,255 --> 00:46:00,090
It's like I'm back at…

931
00:46:05,637 --> 00:46:07,431
Ugh. I feel like I'm gonna start crying.

932
00:46:07,514 --> 00:46:09,558
- Hey, it's not that bad.
- Jin-woo.

933
00:46:13,729 --> 00:46:14,855
It'll get better.

934
00:46:15,564 --> 00:46:16,690
It could be worse.

935
00:46:19,318 --> 00:46:20,486
Just stay positive.

936
00:46:20,569 --> 00:46:22,613
I thought I'd be able to approach her
with confidence,

937
00:46:22,696 --> 00:46:24,740
but the same thing is happening again,

938
00:46:26,658 --> 00:46:29,203
and I feel like I'm going back
to my old self.

939
00:46:32,915 --> 00:46:36,293
- Maybe I was getting ahead of myself.
- No, that's not it at all.

940
00:46:44,426 --> 00:46:46,678
No, to be fair, this isn't easy.

941
00:46:46,762 --> 00:46:49,640
Kudos to Jin-woo for talking
about this so frankly, though.

942
00:46:49,723 --> 00:46:50,557
Yeah.

943
00:46:50,641 --> 00:46:52,976
Yeah. Well, these guys are trying
to navigate relationships

944
00:46:53,060 --> 00:46:54,728
when they've never even been in one.

945
00:46:54,812 --> 00:47:00,275
And I think it's this situation that keeps
reopening these childhood scars of theirs.

946
00:47:00,359 --> 00:47:02,194
And they're losing heart again
all of a sudden.

947
00:47:02,277 --> 00:47:04,613
So in Jin-woo's mind, he's thinking,

948
00:47:04,696 --> 00:47:07,407
"Oh, that's right, Jeong-eun
was so interested in Hyuk-joon."

949
00:47:07,491 --> 00:47:09,201
"I wonder what they're doing right now."

950
00:47:09,284 --> 00:47:11,703
"Have they already become a couple
in Sparks House?"

951
00:47:11,787 --> 00:47:13,872
All these thoughts entering his head,
one after another.

952
00:47:13,956 --> 00:47:17,709
What's so unfortunate is that Han-ju is
crying because she's been hurt by Jin-woo,

953
00:47:17,793 --> 00:47:19,920
while Jin-woo is crying
because of Jeong-eun.

954
00:47:20,003 --> 00:47:21,171
This whole thing is so…

955
00:47:21,255 --> 00:47:23,757
Couldn't Jin-woo just go to Han-ju?

956
00:47:23,841 --> 00:47:25,551
But these guys are all so stubborn.

957
00:47:25,634 --> 00:47:27,010
You've got that right.

958
00:47:27,094 --> 00:47:30,138
From experience, it seems like
all hell breaks loose on the fifth night.

959
00:47:30,222 --> 00:47:31,181
- It does.
- Yep.

960
00:47:31,265 --> 00:47:33,183
- That's right.
- I think they all go through it once.

961
00:47:33,267 --> 00:47:35,477
Because passion builds up inside,
and feelings get deeper.

962
00:47:35,561 --> 00:47:36,603
So true.

963
00:47:36,687 --> 00:47:38,313
- Day six.
- The storm has passed.

964
00:47:38,397 --> 00:47:41,024
- Oh, boy.
- Even the weather is strangely dreary.

965
00:47:41,108 --> 00:47:43,819
LOUNGE

966
00:47:47,155 --> 00:47:49,241
The vibe in the middle
of the table is… Geez!

967
00:47:49,324 --> 00:47:50,284
They're back, right?

968
00:47:50,367 --> 00:47:53,245
- Everyone's faces look so somber.
- They really do.

969
00:47:53,328 --> 00:47:54,872
Oh, they're back.

970
00:47:57,332 --> 00:47:58,667
This is tasty.

971
00:48:02,129 --> 00:48:03,839
Is Su-ji the last one to arrive?

972
00:48:06,675 --> 00:48:08,010
Oh.

973
00:48:08,093 --> 00:48:10,429
- He's here.
- Hyuk-joon makes an entrance.

974
00:48:10,512 --> 00:48:12,055
- He's so relaxed.
- Wait.

975
00:48:12,139 --> 00:48:14,349
There's an empty seat next to Hyun-seo,
but instead he walks

976
00:48:14,433 --> 00:48:16,768
all the way around the table
to sit across from Su-ji.

977
00:48:16,852 --> 00:48:18,312
Smooth, man.

978
00:48:19,563 --> 00:48:21,523
- Hello. What was that?
- Do you want some?

979
00:48:21,607 --> 00:48:22,608
Sure.

980
00:48:24,735 --> 00:48:25,903
Want some jam too?

981
00:48:27,195 --> 00:48:28,196
I'll have one.

982
00:48:28,280 --> 00:48:30,490
The 5 Minute Library won't be open today.

983
00:48:30,574 --> 00:48:33,035
Probably not, since I actually wore
running shoes today.

984
00:48:33,869 --> 00:48:36,038
Ugh. They really need
to talk about this soon.

985
00:48:36,121 --> 00:48:38,665
Yeah, I think I'll end up
leaving before I get a chance to…

986
00:48:40,292 --> 00:48:41,501
Hello.

987
00:48:41,585 --> 00:48:44,004
- Oh, hello.
- Could we have a quick chat later?

988
00:48:44,087 --> 00:48:45,380
- Oh, yeah?
- Yeah.

989
00:48:45,464 --> 00:48:46,715
What's this?

990
00:48:46,798 --> 00:48:49,051
They still have some loose ends to tie up.

991
00:48:49,134 --> 00:48:51,762
'Cause Seung-hyun practically
confessed his feelings to her.

992
00:48:53,055 --> 00:48:54,097
Mmm.

993
00:48:57,684 --> 00:48:59,561
- You know you asked me…
- Yeah?

994
00:49:00,979 --> 00:49:03,649
…if I thought my feelings for you…

995
00:49:04,358 --> 00:49:07,694
if it was possible
they could develop further?

996
00:49:07,778 --> 00:49:08,779
Mmm. Mm-hmm.

997
00:49:11,657 --> 00:49:16,203
I've come to the conclusion that
I don't think that will happen.

998
00:49:16,286 --> 00:49:18,038
- Okay.
- Su-ji…

999
00:49:18,121 --> 00:49:19,331
- Well done.
- Yeah.

1000
00:49:19,414 --> 00:49:21,541
Delivering that message
can't have been easy for her.

1001
00:49:21,625 --> 00:49:22,626
Of course not.

1002
00:49:22,709 --> 00:49:23,752
- Oh, yeah?
- Yeah.

1003
00:49:23,835 --> 00:49:25,587
- You know, I actually…
- Yeah?

1004
00:49:25,671 --> 00:49:29,549
Yeah, it's just, even before you told me,
uh, like…

1005
00:49:29,633 --> 00:49:32,177
- You knew?
- I kind of got that sense.

1006
00:49:32,260 --> 00:49:33,720
So I'm okay.

1007
00:49:33,804 --> 00:49:35,889
- Oh, really?
- And, anyway, um…

1008
00:49:35,973 --> 00:49:39,142
- Thanks for listening to me. Yeah.
- I'm appreciative for letting me know.

1009
00:49:39,226 --> 00:49:40,727
Not at all.

1010
00:49:40,811 --> 00:49:43,772
I hope things won't be awkward between us.

1011
00:49:43,855 --> 00:49:46,608
No, let's continue to be friends.
I still want to be friends with you.

1012
00:49:46,692 --> 00:49:49,403
I like that. That's perfect.
Honestly, I think you're a great friend.

1013
00:49:49,486 --> 00:49:50,862
Me too. Really.

1014
00:49:50,946 --> 00:49:53,949
- Yeah, I'm glad. You're a great friend.
- Best of luck.

1015
00:49:54,032 --> 00:49:56,243
- Yeah, you too. Best of luck.
- Whatever happens. Good luck.

1016
00:49:56,326 --> 00:49:57,160
Thank you.

1017
00:49:57,244 --> 00:49:59,788
- Yeah. I feel so much better now.
- Okay, then.

1018
00:49:59,871 --> 00:50:03,583
I was agonizing since yesterday over
how to tell you. "I have to tell him."

1019
00:50:03,667 --> 00:50:06,294
Gosh, I couldn't even look you in the eye.
I didn't know what to do.

1020
00:50:06,378 --> 00:50:09,423
- Don't take it too seriously.
- Anyways, thanks for that.

1021
00:50:12,592 --> 00:50:15,804
Oh, well, yeah.
Of course I was attracted to her.

1022
00:50:20,017 --> 00:50:23,437
But, you know, what can I do? You know?

1023
00:50:24,521 --> 00:50:27,190
She feels the way she feels,
and I have to respect that.

1024
00:50:27,274 --> 00:50:30,652
Obviously, things didn't work out, but
we still respect each other's feelings.

1025
00:50:31,903 --> 00:50:34,489
- Wow. He respects her feelings.
- Oh, that's so admirable.

1026
00:50:34,573 --> 00:50:36,199
I love that attitude, Seung-hyun.

1027
00:50:36,283 --> 00:50:38,618
Seung-hyun, he's such a nice guy.

1028
00:50:38,702 --> 00:50:39,661
That's nice.

1029
00:50:39,745 --> 00:50:42,372
Yeah, responding in this way
is such a considerate thing to do.

1030
00:50:42,998 --> 00:50:43,999
There is.

1031
00:50:44,082 --> 00:50:45,917
Oh, just since you've been here, you mean?

1032
00:50:46,001 --> 00:50:48,837
- Could I talk to you privately?
- Sure.

1033
00:50:48,920 --> 00:50:51,131
Oh, she's talking to all of them
one by one.

1034
00:50:51,214 --> 00:50:52,716
Oh, is Jung-yun going?

1035
00:50:54,176 --> 00:50:57,387
Wow, Su-ji's not wasting any time.
This was the moment she got back!

1036
00:50:57,471 --> 00:50:59,056
Su-ji's like an assassin right now.

1037
00:50:59,139 --> 00:51:01,308
- She went straight to the purging.
- One by one.

1038
00:51:01,391 --> 00:51:04,352
I can't wait to hear
what she'll say to Jung-yun.

1039
00:51:04,436 --> 00:51:06,021
Mmm…

1040
00:51:09,566 --> 00:51:12,110
There's something I'd like to say to you.

1041
00:51:12,194 --> 00:51:13,195
Okay.

1042
00:51:13,987 --> 00:51:15,530
It's true that…

1043
00:51:16,531 --> 00:51:19,201
you were my top first-impression pick,

1044
00:51:19,826 --> 00:51:21,620
and it's also true…

1045
00:51:23,205 --> 00:51:26,875
that I've been wanting to talk to you
because you continue to grab my interest.

1046
00:51:26,958 --> 00:51:28,502
Because honestly,

1047
00:51:29,461 --> 00:51:31,421
you're the type of guy I usually go for.

1048
00:51:31,505 --> 00:51:34,049
But that doesn't mean you were
the only guy I wanted to get to know.

1049
00:51:34,132 --> 00:51:36,134
That's not how it works.
Especially in the beginning.

1050
00:51:36,218 --> 00:51:38,386
And my feelings developing

1051
00:51:38,470 --> 00:51:40,889
at a slower pace than expected,

1052
00:51:40,972 --> 00:51:44,893
so I just need some more time,

1053
00:51:44,976 --> 00:51:48,271
and it felt like you were moving
faster than me.

1054
00:51:48,939 --> 00:51:51,733
So I wanted to get to know
Hyuk-joon a little,

1055
00:51:51,817 --> 00:51:54,236
just like I wanted to get to know you.

1056
00:51:54,319 --> 00:51:57,405
So that's why I picked him yesterday.

1057
00:51:58,031 --> 00:51:59,199
I also felt…

1058
00:52:00,492 --> 00:52:02,619
like the overall atmosphere was like,

1059
00:52:02,702 --> 00:52:04,704
"Of course Su-ji will pick Jung-yun."

1060
00:52:04,788 --> 00:52:07,374
Like it was becoming
more and more set in stone.

1061
00:52:08,041 --> 00:52:11,586
And I didn't want to feel like
I was being forced into it.

1062
00:52:11,670 --> 00:52:12,587
Right.

1063
00:52:12,671 --> 00:52:15,465
Even though I do still want
to get to know you better.

1064
00:52:15,549 --> 00:52:18,301
- Mmm.
- Because I still do.

1065
00:52:19,219 --> 00:52:23,473
But I want to be honest, and I think
I need a little more time to explore.

1066
00:52:24,349 --> 00:52:25,350
Yeah.

1067
00:52:25,433 --> 00:52:27,144
I wonder how Jung-yun is taking this.

1068
00:52:27,227 --> 00:52:29,020
I know, right? How will he react?

1069
00:52:29,104 --> 00:52:32,440
So, just now,
one of the things you mentioned…

1070
00:52:33,400 --> 00:52:35,110
was the pace of things.

1071
00:52:36,153 --> 00:52:40,031
- I actually tend to move really slowly.
- Oh, really?

1072
00:52:40,115 --> 00:52:41,158
Really?

1073
00:52:41,241 --> 00:52:44,035
But it must not have felt that way to you.

1074
00:52:44,119 --> 00:52:46,872
But I get why you thought I was in a rush.

1075
00:52:46,955 --> 00:52:47,956
Yeah?

1076
00:52:48,582 --> 00:52:52,169
In the past, one reason
my relationships didn't work out

1077
00:52:52,252 --> 00:52:54,379
was because I moved too slowly.

1078
00:52:54,880 --> 00:52:58,967
And it just seems like
the point of being here…

1079
00:52:59,050 --> 00:53:00,427
You wanted to change?

1080
00:53:00,510 --> 00:53:01,511
…was to act

1081
00:53:02,387 --> 00:53:05,140
with a little more courage
and that sort of thing.

1082
00:53:06,600 --> 00:53:09,186
And that's all I was trying to do,

1083
00:53:09,269 --> 00:53:12,272
but I understand why you would think

1084
00:53:12,355 --> 00:53:14,774
the pace was moving too fast for you.

1085
00:53:17,485 --> 00:53:21,448
I really appreciate you telling me
all these things,

1086
00:53:21,531 --> 00:53:22,824
so thank you.

1087
00:53:22,908 --> 00:53:24,534
Thank you for listening.

1088
00:53:24,618 --> 00:53:25,619
Of course.

1089
00:53:27,704 --> 00:53:30,123
Wow, these conversations
are just so frank.

1090
00:53:30,207 --> 00:53:31,458
That was great.

1091
00:53:31,541 --> 00:53:34,044
They're finally communicating properly.

1092
00:53:34,127 --> 00:53:35,754
This is a good experience for them both.

1093
00:53:35,837 --> 00:53:37,589
Learning to understand
different perspectives.

1094
00:53:37,672 --> 00:53:40,175
I'm impressed by Jung-yun,
because had it been me,

1095
00:53:40,258 --> 00:53:42,886
I would be too resentful
to even look at Su-ji.

1096
00:53:42,969 --> 00:53:45,263
- That's understandable.
- I would've been so upset.

1097
00:53:45,347 --> 00:53:47,807
I'm so glad that Jung-yun was firm
and said,

1098
00:53:47,891 --> 00:53:49,976
"Yeah, I understand.
I think I was moving too fast."

1099
00:53:50,060 --> 00:53:50,894
Yeah.

1100
00:53:51,728 --> 00:53:53,813
I have a lot on my mind too.

1101
00:53:54,773 --> 00:53:57,609
Actually, ever since yesterday,

1102
00:53:58,693 --> 00:54:01,321
I've lost quite a lot of attraction
to Hyuk-joon.

1103
00:54:02,030 --> 00:54:03,198
Mmm.

1104
00:54:03,281 --> 00:54:04,699
Yeah. Because, like,

1105
00:54:05,283 --> 00:54:07,035
when we were on our date,

1106
00:54:08,078 --> 00:54:12,791
he totally made it sound like
I was the only one in his heart.

1107
00:54:13,667 --> 00:54:17,712
He was all like, "I don't even remember
who I chose as my second pick."

1108
00:54:17,796 --> 00:54:21,591
"That's how significant
my first pick is to me," and so on.

1109
00:54:21,675 --> 00:54:25,178
But then yesterday, we were on
a three-way date with Han-ju,

1110
00:54:25,262 --> 00:54:28,765
and the whole date,
he was really attentive to her.

1111
00:54:29,516 --> 00:54:32,143
I mean, I think he was trying
to treat us fairly,

1112
00:54:32,227 --> 00:54:35,188
but I was a bit like,
"Is that really necessary?"

1113
00:54:36,648 --> 00:54:39,317
And then after seeing the way
he was waiting on Su-ji

1114
00:54:39,401 --> 00:54:41,653
hand and foot this morning…

1115
00:54:41,736 --> 00:54:43,571
A SHORT WHILE AGO

1116
00:54:45,031 --> 00:54:46,241
You're done, right?

1117
00:54:46,324 --> 00:54:48,159
Mm-hmm. I'll put it back.

1118
00:54:48,243 --> 00:54:49,244
Okay.

1119
00:54:49,327 --> 00:54:51,037
Oh, she noticed, of course.

1120
00:54:51,121 --> 00:54:53,248
Of course she's going to notice that.

1121
00:54:54,332 --> 00:54:55,375
Wow.

1122
00:54:59,587 --> 00:55:01,298
That made me realize

1123
00:55:02,132 --> 00:55:05,510
he's the kind of guy
that's nice to all the girls.

1124
00:55:05,593 --> 00:55:09,514
And now that I've witnessed that
two separate times,

1125
00:55:09,597 --> 00:55:11,850
It's just, I really hate that type of guy.

1126
00:55:11,933 --> 00:55:13,685
- I hate smooth talkers.
- Right.

1127
00:55:13,768 --> 00:55:19,399
So now I'm thinking he might not actually
be who I really thought he was.

1128
00:55:20,817 --> 00:55:23,945
I see why you would feel that way,
given all the things he said to you.

1129
00:55:24,029 --> 00:55:26,948
Yeah, but you know, looking back,
he was very up-front

1130
00:55:27,032 --> 00:55:29,951
about his feelings for me
when we were on dates,

1131
00:55:30,035 --> 00:55:31,369
but once the dates were over,

1132
00:55:31,453 --> 00:55:33,538
I feel like it was always me

1133
00:55:33,621 --> 00:55:36,082
talking to him first
and taking the initiative.

1134
00:55:36,166 --> 00:55:40,045
Even the others said
that it was obvious that I liked him.

1135
00:55:41,046 --> 00:55:44,341
But no one ever said it was obvious
that he liked me, so…

1136
00:55:44,424 --> 00:55:46,009
I'm starting to think

1137
00:55:46,926 --> 00:55:49,471
that maybe I've been played.

1138
00:55:50,221 --> 00:55:53,433
- It was definitely Hyun-seo at the start.
- Exactly.

1139
00:55:53,516 --> 00:55:56,227
I have to say, it seems Hyuk-joon
and Hyun-seo both moved too quickly.

1140
00:55:56,311 --> 00:55:57,395
They moved too fast.

1141
00:55:57,479 --> 00:55:59,397
Hyuk-joon was like,
"I only have eyes for you."

1142
00:55:59,481 --> 00:56:00,315
He totally was.

1143
00:56:00,398 --> 00:56:05,153
So to see the way he's behaving right now
must be a real blow to Hyun-seo.

1144
00:56:05,236 --> 00:56:07,030
Right, she thought she was special to him,

1145
00:56:07,113 --> 00:56:09,532
so when she saw him act that way
to the other girls as well,

1146
00:56:09,616 --> 00:56:10,950
she was like, "What's going on here?"

1147
00:56:11,034 --> 00:56:13,036
The other concern is that
Hyun-seo and Hyuk-joon

1148
00:56:13,119 --> 00:56:15,288
aren't even making eye contact right now.

1149
00:56:15,372 --> 00:56:17,957
I'm worried they're really going to
fall out at this rate.

1150
00:56:18,041 --> 00:56:20,960
But Hyun-seo has said that
multiple times now.

1151
00:56:21,044 --> 00:56:23,963
And resenting him and bad-mouthing him,
what does all that mean?

1152
00:56:24,047 --> 00:56:25,924
- She still has feelings for him.
- It's love.

1153
00:56:26,007 --> 00:56:27,759
I wonder how these two will end up?

1154
00:56:27,842 --> 00:56:30,303
- They need to talk more.
- They need to talk it out.

1155
00:56:39,354 --> 00:56:41,314
- He is not subtle.
- Why is she whispering?

1156
00:56:41,398 --> 00:56:43,149
- What?
- I want to hear too.

1157
00:56:43,233 --> 00:56:45,235
- Oh, it's a secret.
- She can't tell you. It's a secret.

1158
00:56:45,318 --> 00:56:47,946
- If you want to know, you have to pay.
- Right. Oh, I have to pay?

1159
00:56:48,530 --> 00:56:50,824
- Ah. And when I don't have my wallet.
- Exactly.

1160
00:56:52,534 --> 00:56:56,287
Ugh, why is Hyun-seo dressed
like a tragic heroine again?

1161
00:56:56,371 --> 00:56:57,580
This is kind of…

1162
00:56:58,456 --> 00:57:01,418
"How could you have cast aside
all your feelings for me?"

1163
00:57:02,168 --> 00:57:04,003
"Our love is a thing of the past."

1164
00:57:04,087 --> 00:57:06,548
"Then what of all the words
you spoke unto me?"

1165
00:57:06,631 --> 00:57:08,716
- "You were pleased, were you not?"
- That's spot-on.

1166
00:57:08,800 --> 00:57:10,176
"I even wore Another 13!"

1167
00:57:10,844 --> 00:57:12,303
Oh, my God.

1168
00:57:12,387 --> 00:57:14,931
Stop it, Eun-ji. That's enough.

1169
00:57:15,723 --> 00:57:16,724
Oh, dear.

1170
00:57:17,308 --> 00:57:19,018
I was ready for another sprint today.

1171
00:57:19,102 --> 00:57:20,937
Han-ju's looking refreshed, isn't she?

1172
00:57:21,563 --> 00:57:22,939
Right?

1173
00:57:23,022 --> 00:57:24,023
Yes?

1174
00:57:24,107 --> 00:57:25,483
Ugh.

1175
00:57:26,276 --> 00:57:28,445
- It has to be mutual!
- Oh, no. What will happen now?

1176
00:57:28,528 --> 00:57:30,613
ONE-ON-ONE DATES FOR COUPLES
WHO SELECT EACH OTHER

1177
00:57:30,697 --> 00:57:32,365
This is exactly what we needed.

1178
00:57:32,449 --> 00:57:34,826
- We haven't had this yet.
- Yeah, that's right.

1179
00:57:34,909 --> 00:57:36,494
To go on a date, the picks must be mutual?

1180
00:57:36,578 --> 00:57:37,412
Correct.

1181
00:57:37,495 --> 00:57:40,707
This time, same as last time, the thing
to watch is who Hyuk-joon will choose.

1182
00:57:40,790 --> 00:57:43,543
Oh, my God. What if it's Su-ji
and Hyuk-joon again? Please, no.

1183
00:57:44,794 --> 00:57:46,754
I don't know
why everything's so difficult.

1184
00:57:46,838 --> 00:57:49,299
Honestly, I was worried
that we wouldn't match.

1185
00:57:51,676 --> 00:57:55,388
Um, I feel like I have
a clearer sense of direction now,

1186
00:57:55,972 --> 00:57:57,390
so I chose Seo-yoon.

1187
00:57:59,142 --> 00:58:01,644
The odds aren't great
with one-on-one matching,

1188
00:58:01,728 --> 00:58:03,146
so I didn't expect much.

1189
00:58:03,897 --> 00:58:06,149
My current goal is to go on a date

1190
00:58:06,232 --> 00:58:08,234
with someone other than Hyuk-joon.

1191
00:58:09,360 --> 00:58:11,654
I didn't even have to think about it.

1192
00:58:11,738 --> 00:58:13,406
My mind was already made up.

1193
00:58:13,490 --> 00:58:15,366
- Huh?
- His mind's made up?

1194
00:58:15,450 --> 00:58:18,620
I have a strange feeling that
Su-ji and Jung-yun will match.

1195
00:58:19,245 --> 00:58:22,749
If Hyuk-joon has made up his mind,
he should tell Hyun-seo right away.

1196
00:58:22,832 --> 00:58:26,294
Gosh, whenever he looks at Su-ji,
his dimples come out.

1197
00:58:26,377 --> 00:58:27,212
Yeah.

1198
00:58:27,295 --> 00:58:30,590
No matter what, we should have Soo-hyun
and Tae-hoon out on a date together.

1199
00:58:30,673 --> 00:58:33,301
- They should definitely go on a date.
- Blueberry couple on a date.

1200
00:58:33,384 --> 00:58:35,303
How many people will be joining?

1201
00:58:37,138 --> 00:58:39,015
- I got a message.
- Oh, boy, what will happen?

1202
00:58:39,098 --> 00:58:41,809
- Oh, my God.
- This is the most important date.

1203
00:58:41,893 --> 00:58:43,770
TAE-HOON & SOO-HYUN
YOU'VE MATCHED ON A 1:1 DATE

1204
00:58:43,853 --> 00:58:45,647
All right, way to go you two!

1205
00:58:45,730 --> 00:58:46,648
It's not me.

1206
00:58:46,731 --> 00:58:48,274
- Oh, my God!
- Way to go!

1207
00:58:48,358 --> 00:58:50,109
Soo-hyun looks a little shy.

1208
00:58:50,193 --> 00:58:51,611
That's 'cause she's shy.

1209
00:58:51,694 --> 00:58:53,321
What are you doing? Get that out of there!

1210
00:58:53,404 --> 00:58:55,323
- They can't look at each other.
- What's up with them?

1211
00:58:55,406 --> 00:58:57,659
- They're like figures in a wax museum.
- They're so cute.

1212
00:58:57,742 --> 00:58:59,452
I was stoked.

1213
00:58:59,536 --> 00:59:01,788
Since I'm attracted to him,

1214
00:59:01,871 --> 00:59:04,457
I thought it would be fun.

1215
00:59:04,541 --> 00:59:07,710
I've been wanting to spend
some real time with her on a date.

1216
00:59:09,504 --> 00:59:11,589
Jin-woo.

1217
00:59:11,673 --> 00:59:15,260
I submitted An Jeong-eun
as my answer as soon as I got the text.

1218
00:59:15,343 --> 00:59:18,346
Having talked things over
and then slept on it,

1219
00:59:18,429 --> 00:59:21,266
my head felt a lot clearer,
so there was no hesitation.

1220
00:59:23,059 --> 00:59:24,310
JIN-WOO & JEONG-EUN
YOU'VE MATCHED

1221
00:59:24,394 --> 00:59:26,229
- He must be so happy.
- Yes!

1222
00:59:26,312 --> 00:59:27,730
I did get a message saying I've matched.

1223
00:59:27,814 --> 00:59:30,567
Oh, really? That's great.

1224
00:59:30,650 --> 00:59:33,236
I'm so glad. Jin-woo must be stoked.

1225
00:59:33,319 --> 00:59:34,821
How exciting!

1226
00:59:34,904 --> 00:59:36,364
I chose Jin-woo.

1227
00:59:36,447 --> 00:59:40,076
I chose him because I felt
I needed to talk to him more,

1228
00:59:40,159 --> 00:59:42,704
so when I got the chance, I chose him.

1229
00:59:42,787 --> 00:59:46,499
- In reality, Jin-woo had no reason to cry.
- Exactly. It turned out great for him.

1230
00:59:46,583 --> 00:59:48,668
- Oh, here we go. Watch.
- Okay.

1231
00:59:48,751 --> 00:59:52,005
I asked Jung-yun out on a one-on-one date.

1232
00:59:52,088 --> 00:59:53,006
See?

1233
00:59:53,089 --> 00:59:54,173
Oh, really?

1234
00:59:54,882 --> 00:59:57,427
I felt I'd talked a lot with Hyuk-joon

1235
00:59:57,510 --> 00:59:59,679
in Sparks House yesterday,

1236
00:59:59,762 --> 01:00:02,974
but I hadn't talked as much
with Jung-yun in comparison,

1237
01:00:03,057 --> 01:00:06,060
so I thought, "I really should
spend more time with him."

1238
01:00:06,144 --> 01:00:08,187
Oops. I think we have a mismatch here.

1239
01:00:08,271 --> 01:00:10,148
Ugh! Because Jung-yun could
be feeling salty.

1240
01:00:10,231 --> 01:00:11,858
Don't think Jung-yun will pick her?

1241
01:00:11,941 --> 01:00:13,151
I'm not really sure…

1242
01:00:13,234 --> 01:00:14,611
JUST BEFORE THE DATE SELECTION

1243
01:00:14,694 --> 01:00:17,030
…who I should choose.

1244
01:00:17,113 --> 01:00:19,032
You don't think you'll pick her?

1245
01:00:21,367 --> 01:00:22,994
I feel like…

1246
01:00:23,911 --> 01:00:26,497
there's a knife twisting in an old wound.

1247
01:00:28,333 --> 01:00:32,128
So I don't think I can face her
and look her in the eye.

1248
01:00:32,629 --> 01:00:35,632
- Oh, I really hope he chooses her.
- Dude, don't give up!

1249
01:00:43,640 --> 01:00:44,849
JUNG-YUN & SU-JI
YOU'VE MATCHED

1250
01:00:44,932 --> 01:00:46,309
- Awesome!
- Thank God.

1251
01:00:46,392 --> 01:00:48,394
Nice. That's great.

1252
01:00:48,478 --> 01:00:50,563
Despite everything,

1253
01:00:50,647 --> 01:00:53,399
I worked up the courage
to come on the show,

1254
01:00:53,483 --> 01:00:57,278
so I decided I should just be brave

1255
01:00:57,362 --> 01:00:59,405
and face her with honesty.

1256
01:01:00,198 --> 01:01:03,159
And that's why I submitted her name.

1257
01:01:04,535 --> 01:01:05,870
Of course I'm happy.

1258
01:01:05,953 --> 01:01:09,582
If Su-ji had chosen someone else,
this date wouldn't be happening,

1259
01:01:09,666 --> 01:01:11,501
and I'd just be here alone.

1260
01:01:12,210 --> 01:01:14,003
But that wasn't the case,

1261
01:01:14,087 --> 01:01:17,465
so… it was a relief, and I'm very happy.

1262
01:01:17,548 --> 01:01:18,883
Finally, Jung-yun's smiling!

1263
01:01:18,966 --> 01:01:20,760
First he's smiled since yesterday.

1264
01:01:20,843 --> 01:01:22,428
Good job, Jung-yun.

1265
01:01:22,512 --> 01:01:25,682
Do you think this date is
maybe what Su-ji considers

1266
01:01:25,765 --> 01:01:28,101
as, like, the deadline
for figuring out her feelings?

1267
01:01:28,184 --> 01:01:30,561
- A way of forcing herself to decide?
- To get to her final decision?

1268
01:01:30,645 --> 01:01:32,105
Right.

1269
01:01:32,772 --> 01:01:34,315
- Is that the results?
- Yes.

1270
01:01:34,399 --> 01:01:35,274
Oh, really?

1271
01:01:41,322 --> 01:01:44,951
I submitted Hyuk-joon as my desired date.

1272
01:01:45,034 --> 01:01:46,661
- Very doubtful.
- No way.

1273
01:01:49,455 --> 01:01:51,541
- He did get a response.
- I don't see this happening.

1274
01:01:51,624 --> 01:01:54,544
- Let's see.
- It's not a match, I don't think.

1275
01:01:54,627 --> 01:01:56,879
Hyuk-joon, I don't think
you're going on a date.

1276
01:01:58,005 --> 01:02:00,675
CHOI HYUK-JOON & LEE HAN-JU
YOU'VE MATCHED ON A 1:1 DATE

1277
01:02:05,388 --> 01:02:06,597
What the heck?

1278
01:02:07,306 --> 01:02:08,725
Wait, what?

1279
01:02:08,808 --> 01:02:12,395
Honestly, I do not think
that guy is in his right mind.

1280
01:02:13,980 --> 01:02:16,524
- It's like he's going…
- What do you mean?

1281
01:02:16,607 --> 01:02:20,695
"I'm going to go on a date with
all the participants without prejudice."

1282
01:02:20,778 --> 01:02:23,698
- So he really is on tour?
- He wasn't joking. He really is on tour.

1283
01:02:23,781 --> 01:02:25,825
Is he on a national tour?

1284
01:02:25,908 --> 01:02:29,078
Okay, so from where I'm sitting, it's over
between Hyuk-joon and Hyun-seo.

1285
01:02:29,162 --> 01:02:31,497
He's been wanting to go
on a date with Han-ju,

1286
01:02:31,581 --> 01:02:34,751
who was originally his second choice,
to get to know her better.

1287
01:02:35,626 --> 01:02:38,880
But before he managed to do that,
Su-ji aggressively entered the scene.

1288
01:02:38,963 --> 01:02:41,758
When the day before, he wanted
to go on a date with Jeong-eun.

1289
01:02:42,467 --> 01:02:44,677
- One date with this girl…
- He never even mentioned this.

1290
01:02:44,761 --> 01:02:47,388
- Along the way, it turned into a tour.
- It happens.

1291
01:02:47,472 --> 01:02:52,101
My guess is that he's still trying
to figure out what he likes.

1292
01:02:52,185 --> 01:02:55,396
But to be honest, he's not easy to defend.

1293
01:02:55,480 --> 01:02:57,064
No, you're right. He's not.

1294
01:02:57,148 --> 01:03:00,193
But if you really think about it,
all Hyuk-joon's trying to do

1295
01:03:00,276 --> 01:03:02,987
is get to know
the people he's interested in.

1296
01:03:03,070 --> 01:03:05,990
The only issue is he's over-the-top
expressing of his feelings,

1297
01:03:06,073 --> 01:03:08,326
but that stems from having
never been in a relationship before.

1298
01:03:08,409 --> 01:03:10,411
- It's all just part of the process.
- Totally.

1299
01:03:10,495 --> 01:03:14,123
CHOI HYUK-JOON & LEE HAN-JU
YOU'VE MATCHED ON A 1:1 DATE

1300
01:03:14,207 --> 01:03:16,793
I was determined to have
a conversation with Han-ju today.

1301
01:03:17,460 --> 01:03:19,587
I was really interested to hear her story.

1302
01:03:20,922 --> 01:03:24,091
Especially since I'd already talked
a lot with Jeong-eun and Su-ji.

1303
01:03:25,343 --> 01:03:27,220
You're so lucky you're matched.

1304
01:03:27,303 --> 01:03:29,639
Right? I'm excited to go on a date.

1305
01:03:32,266 --> 01:03:34,477
I was happy to receive the text

1306
01:03:34,560 --> 01:03:36,896
that said I'd been matched with Hyuk-joon.

1307
01:03:36,979 --> 01:03:41,359
I was glad that he seemed
genuinely interested

1308
01:03:41,442 --> 01:03:43,569
to find out more about me.

1309
01:03:43,653 --> 01:03:47,907
WHAT'S THE REASON FOR
NOT CHOOSING JIN-WOO?

1310
01:03:49,242 --> 01:03:51,869
I just don't want to get hurt again, and…

1311
01:03:53,663 --> 01:03:55,456
I just don't want to get hurt again.

1312
01:03:56,833 --> 01:03:59,293
I wasn't shocked or anything

1313
01:03:59,377 --> 01:04:01,879
that he'd gone on a date
with someone else,

1314
01:04:01,963 --> 01:04:04,715
because it's reasonable to want
to get to know people.

1315
01:04:05,258 --> 01:04:07,385
But if he does that again tomorrow,

1316
01:04:07,468 --> 01:04:11,764
I think my interest in him
would suffer quite a lot.

1317
01:04:11,848 --> 01:04:15,101
I was quite surprised
by Hyuk-joon and Han-ju,

1318
01:04:15,184 --> 01:04:17,061
because Hyuk-joon had told me that

1319
01:04:17,144 --> 01:04:19,897
he hadn't really enjoyed
the three-way date.

1320
01:04:21,148 --> 01:04:23,776
So I wondered why he was going
on a date with Han-ju

1321
01:04:23,860 --> 01:04:25,987
after telling me that
he hadn't enjoyed himself.

1322
01:04:26,070 --> 01:04:28,030
The fact that they'd matched
really shocked me.

1323
01:04:28,114 --> 01:04:32,827
I was like, "What's going on here?
I really don't know anything, do I?"

1324
01:04:32,910 --> 01:04:34,120
This is how Su-ji would take it.

1325
01:04:34,203 --> 01:04:35,037
She's thinking,

1326
01:04:35,121 --> 01:04:37,915
"So then what were the moments
we shared in Sparks House yesterday?"

1327
01:04:39,208 --> 01:04:41,294
Looks like today is going to be
another headache.

1328
01:04:51,554 --> 01:04:53,681
I knew I wouldn't be going on a date.

1329
01:04:54,432 --> 01:04:58,978
It was so expected
that it doesn't even bother me.

1330
01:04:59,061 --> 01:05:00,855
But at least I have no regrets.

1331
01:05:02,189 --> 01:05:03,691
It's now been confirmed.

1332
01:05:03,774 --> 01:05:06,652
I couldn't pull myself
away from the electric blanket.

1333
01:05:06,736 --> 01:05:08,362
That's a surprising number of dates.

1334
01:05:08,446 --> 01:05:11,240
A whopping four couples
are going on one-on-one dates. Wow.

1335
01:05:11,324 --> 01:05:12,575
And this is only day six.

1336
01:05:12,658 --> 01:05:14,327
- See you later.
- Bye.

1337
01:05:14,410 --> 01:05:15,828
See you later. Good luck.

1338
01:05:17,580 --> 01:05:19,790
Aw, Soo-hyun's all dressed up
in light colors.

1339
01:05:19,874 --> 01:05:21,584
Cute to see her dressed up like this.

1340
01:05:21,667 --> 01:05:24,045
- She usually doesn't do that.
- Yeah.

1341
01:05:25,087 --> 01:05:27,840
- What is it?
- You don't think it'll rain, do you?

1342
01:05:27,924 --> 01:05:29,884
We're driving anyway, so it'll be okay.
Let's go.

1343
01:05:29,967 --> 01:05:31,135
All right.

1344
01:05:31,218 --> 01:05:33,763
What was that?
Did Tae-hoon not want to wait for her?

1345
01:05:33,846 --> 01:05:35,306
I was waiting for ages.

1346
01:05:35,389 --> 01:05:37,516
I thought you'd already left.

1347
01:05:37,600 --> 01:05:39,435
- Left without you?
- I did. I thought you were gone.

1348
01:05:39,518 --> 01:05:42,396
They already know
there's a mutual attraction,

1349
01:05:42,480 --> 01:05:43,981
so they must be so excited.

1350
01:05:44,065 --> 01:05:46,150
Yeah, there's giddy excitement,
but with a friend vibe.

1351
01:05:46,233 --> 01:05:47,068
Right.

1352
01:05:47,151 --> 01:05:49,946
- Let's do this.
- Ooh, are you driving?

1353
01:05:50,029 --> 01:05:52,782
- Leave it to me.
- Oh, it's cold.

1354
01:05:57,286 --> 01:05:59,330
- Let's go slow.
- Sure thing.

1355
01:06:02,208 --> 01:06:04,919
- Did you check your mailbox today?
- Yes!

1356
01:06:05,002 --> 01:06:07,004
Wait, did he leave her a letter?

1357
01:06:07,088 --> 01:06:08,589
It was really well written.

1358
01:06:08,673 --> 01:06:11,300
Yeah, well, I made a special effort.

1359
01:06:12,134 --> 01:06:14,387
- When did you write it?
- This morning.

1360
01:06:14,887 --> 01:06:16,430
6 A.M.

1361
01:06:17,598 --> 01:06:19,976
- What are you eating, Jae-seo?
- I think it's fried chicken.

1362
01:06:20,059 --> 01:06:21,978
He's eating chicken
before the sun's even up?

1363
01:06:22,603 --> 01:06:24,480
- Writing at that hour?
- At the crack of dawn.

1364
01:06:24,563 --> 01:06:25,398
That's impressive.

1365
01:06:26,107 --> 01:06:28,359
He got up early to write her that letter.

1366
01:06:37,326 --> 01:06:40,121
Oh! A letter. Yeah, it must be mine.

1367
01:06:40,204 --> 01:06:42,123
- I think I'm gonna pass out.
- Earlier…

1368
01:06:42,206 --> 01:06:43,290
- Who is it?
- Who is it?

1369
01:06:43,374 --> 01:06:44,667
- Who is it?
- It's no big deal.

1370
01:06:44,750 --> 01:06:46,877
Oh. "You wanted to know
whose diary I'd read

1371
01:06:46,961 --> 01:06:49,588
in the 5 Minute Library recently."

1372
01:06:49,672 --> 01:06:52,883
Oh, so yesterday,
I asked him whose diary he'd read

1373
01:06:52,967 --> 01:06:54,719
in the 5 Minute Library,

1374
01:06:54,802 --> 01:06:57,138
and he told me he'd tell me later.

1375
01:06:57,221 --> 01:06:59,932
So he wrote to tell me that he'd looked
at mine because he was curious.

1376
01:07:00,016 --> 01:07:01,684
So Tae-hoon had a plan.

1377
01:07:01,767 --> 01:07:03,436
Must've been something we didn't see.

1378
01:07:04,103 --> 01:07:05,688
I only just saw this now.

1379
01:07:05,771 --> 01:07:08,149
I wish I had checked sooner.

1380
01:07:11,402 --> 01:07:13,487
It felt great.

1381
01:07:13,571 --> 01:07:16,824
I'd been doubtful that anyone would read
my diary in the 5 Minute Library.

1382
01:07:16,907 --> 01:07:20,244
I was very excited when I was leaving
for the one-on-one date.

1383
01:07:20,327 --> 01:07:23,581
- Aw, Tae-hoon's such a romantic.
- Which would you have preferred?

1384
01:07:23,664 --> 01:07:25,458
Would you rather
get an answer in the moment

1385
01:07:25,541 --> 01:07:26,876
or a letter with his decision later?

1386
01:07:26,959 --> 01:07:30,171
- I think the letter is more touching.
- Yeah, this is the right move.

1387
01:07:30,254 --> 01:07:33,299
Yeah. Because you get the sense
that he really put a lot of thought

1388
01:07:33,382 --> 01:07:34,467
into how to tell her.

1389
01:07:34,550 --> 01:07:36,552
- You're right.
- He's communicating by letter.

1390
01:07:36,635 --> 01:07:38,721
- I love it.
- Love it. It's a good move.

1391
01:07:38,804 --> 01:07:41,807
As long as he doesn't bring up
anyone else while he's writing to her.

1392
01:07:41,891 --> 01:07:44,977
The weird thing is,
there's nothing to be nervous about here.

1393
01:07:45,061 --> 01:07:48,105
- Look how nice this place is.
- This place is pretty.

1394
01:07:50,608 --> 01:07:51,817
Thank you for driving.

1395
01:07:52,818 --> 01:07:54,153
A round of applause.

1396
01:07:55,154 --> 01:07:56,655
I felt comfortable and safe.

1397
01:07:56,739 --> 01:07:58,699
- So it was really nice.
- Well, good.

1398
01:07:58,783 --> 01:08:01,160
Yikes. It's actually palpable
how shy they are.

1399
01:08:01,243 --> 01:08:03,120
Oh, Soo-hyun…

1400
01:08:03,204 --> 01:08:05,164
She can't even look him in the eye.

1401
01:08:05,247 --> 01:08:06,499
Well, he just stares at her.

1402
01:08:07,249 --> 01:08:09,585
So, when you went to
the Post Office this morning…

1403
01:08:09,668 --> 01:08:12,797
- I'm telling you, I was so surprised.
- …did you expect there to be any mail?

1404
01:08:12,880 --> 01:08:14,090
- No.
- Not at all?

1405
01:08:14,173 --> 01:08:15,758
Because you wouldn't tell me.

1406
01:08:15,841 --> 01:08:18,094
I asked you whose you'd read
in the 5 Minute Library,

1407
01:08:18,177 --> 01:08:20,387
you just kept saying,
"I'll tell you later."

1408
01:08:20,471 --> 01:08:23,516
So I was like, "Whose would he read
but only tell me later?"

1409
01:08:24,266 --> 01:08:26,769
- Thank you for reading mine.
- You were a little antsy, huh?

1410
01:08:26,852 --> 01:08:28,604
I was really touched, to be honest.

1411
01:08:28,687 --> 01:08:31,524
Because I never thought
anyone would read mine, so…

1412
01:08:32,191 --> 01:08:33,901
I was honestly quite touched.

1413
01:08:35,903 --> 01:08:37,780
It wasn't that deep. It's not a big deal.

1414
01:08:37,863 --> 01:08:39,240
No, of course I was touched.

1415
01:08:39,323 --> 01:08:42,284
Come on, you used two coupons on it,
and you only get three coupons.

1416
01:08:42,368 --> 01:08:44,745
Exactly. It was a huge gesture.

1417
01:08:44,829 --> 01:08:45,830
Thank you.

1418
01:08:47,039 --> 01:08:50,126
Yeah, it took two coupons,
but it was totally worth it.

1419
01:08:50,209 --> 01:08:52,002
Oh, that was a cute flex.

1420
01:08:54,004 --> 01:08:57,133
So, what did you think
when you first saw it?

1421
01:08:57,216 --> 01:08:58,551
- After reading it?
- Yeah.

1422
01:08:58,634 --> 01:09:02,054
Were you like, "Uh-oh!"
Or were you like, "Oh, this is nice."

1423
01:09:06,350 --> 01:09:08,477
BEST ROTATION DATE CONVERSATION?
KIM TAE-HOON

1424
01:09:12,398 --> 01:09:14,525
- His face…
- It was, "This is nice."

1425
01:09:14,608 --> 01:09:16,235
- "This is nice"?
- Mm-hmm.

1426
01:09:17,069 --> 01:09:18,070
Gotcha.

1427
01:09:19,864 --> 01:09:21,907
But when I saw you had put my name for

1428
01:09:21,991 --> 01:09:24,910
"the person you had the best conversation
with" question, I was like--

1429
01:09:24,994 --> 01:09:26,537
- "Oh, success"?
- "Success!"

1430
01:09:27,705 --> 01:09:30,791
- So I guess I did well in my confessional.
- Mm-hmm. Yeah, for sure.

1431
01:09:30,875 --> 01:09:32,459
You did well, honestly.

1432
01:09:37,798 --> 01:09:39,592
Well, this is nice.
Just being out and about

1433
01:09:39,675 --> 01:09:42,720
is so much better
than being stuck on site.

1434
01:09:42,803 --> 01:09:45,222
Earlier, when we got that text,
I was thinking, like,

1435
01:09:45,306 --> 01:09:48,017
"Great, what should I do in here today?
Should I just take a nap?"

1436
01:09:48,100 --> 01:09:51,061
If it had been another,
what do they call it, random date…

1437
01:09:51,145 --> 01:09:54,023
if I had another of those, I would've
been like, "Ugh, this is pointless."

1438
01:09:54,106 --> 01:09:55,441
Me too. Like, "Wah-wah…"

1439
01:09:55,524 --> 01:09:57,443
"It's pretty much been decided,
so what's the point?"

1440
01:09:57,526 --> 01:09:58,986
Exactly. What's the point?

1441
01:10:00,905 --> 01:10:02,198
Do you think it'll change?

1442
01:10:02,740 --> 01:10:03,657
- My pick?
- Yeah.

1443
01:10:03,741 --> 01:10:05,284
Like, do you think I'd change my mind?

1444
01:10:07,620 --> 01:10:09,997
Um, aren't I talking to you right now?

1445
01:10:12,917 --> 01:10:14,335
Aw, I love this.

1446
01:10:14,418 --> 01:10:16,086
- Oh.
- Well, that's why.

1447
01:10:16,170 --> 01:10:19,089
- Nice. What a great answer.
- Right?

1448
01:10:19,173 --> 01:10:21,467
- Aren't I talking to you right now?
- Mmm.

1449
01:10:21,550 --> 01:10:23,052
You liked that answer, didn't you?

1450
01:10:23,135 --> 01:10:25,221
Yeah, I was gonna give you
a hundred points for that one.

1451
01:10:25,304 --> 01:10:26,180
Okay, okay.

1452
01:10:26,263 --> 01:10:28,224
- Oh, Tae-hoon.
- What is it with this guy?

1453
01:10:28,307 --> 01:10:29,558
He's really sweet with this girl.

1454
01:10:29,642 --> 01:10:32,978
The way he's gazing lovingly
at Soo-hyun is so awesome.

1455
01:10:33,062 --> 01:10:35,522
- He's the best at this.
- He's the best, he's the best.

1456
01:10:35,606 --> 01:10:37,149
Kim Tae-hoon is the best of the lot.

1457
01:10:37,233 --> 01:10:40,486
That's why he's the game changer.
And I had completely forgotten about that.

1458
01:10:40,569 --> 01:10:42,321
Didn't he trigger
a DEFCON alert at the start?

1459
01:10:42,404 --> 01:10:45,199
That's what I'm saying. That's why
he's so good to the girl he likes.

1460
01:10:45,282 --> 01:10:46,533
So he's the real deal.

1461
01:10:48,077 --> 01:10:50,829
What about you? I bet
you're at the top of everyone's list.

1462
01:10:51,455 --> 01:10:54,166
Maybe. But I think
I've got it figured out.

1463
01:10:54,250 --> 01:10:55,376
I don't think it'll change.

1464
01:10:56,794 --> 01:10:59,672
Yeah, I don't think there'll be
any changes from now on.

1465
01:10:59,755 --> 01:11:01,215
- The way I feel right now.
- What?

1466
01:11:01,298 --> 01:11:03,550
Wouldn't you say so?

1467
01:11:05,219 --> 01:11:07,680
Oh, look. He can't even speak.

1468
01:11:07,763 --> 01:11:09,306
There you go.

1469
01:11:09,390 --> 01:11:11,892
Time to go. Just leave.
Leave ahead of time.

1470
01:11:11,976 --> 01:11:13,894
Oh, I wanted to ask you…

1471
01:11:13,978 --> 01:11:17,731
Since you're either in Daejeon or Seoul,
are you okay with long distance?

1472
01:11:17,815 --> 01:11:19,900
- Long distance?
- Like if I didn't live in Seoul?

1473
01:11:19,984 --> 01:11:21,735
She's discussing practicalities.

1474
01:11:21,819 --> 01:11:24,154
- Because I'm actually in Daegu.
- Oh.

1475
01:11:24,863 --> 01:11:28,409
If it happened,
I think I'd give it a go before deciding.

1476
01:11:28,492 --> 01:11:29,827
Mmm.

1477
01:11:30,703 --> 01:11:33,622
I've never tried it,
so there's no need to fear it prematurely.

1478
01:11:33,706 --> 01:11:34,707
Mmm.

1479
01:11:35,541 --> 01:11:37,668
Daegu doesn't take that long
from Dongdaegu Station.

1480
01:11:37,751 --> 01:11:39,253
Tae-hoon's saying all the right things.

1481
01:11:39,336 --> 01:11:41,547
Seriously, it doesn't take that long
from Dongdaegu Station.

1482
01:11:41,630 --> 01:11:43,507
- I'll drive him there myself.
- Yeah.

1483
01:11:43,590 --> 01:11:45,551
- Oh, Tae-hoon's good with words.
- That's what I said.

1484
01:11:45,634 --> 01:11:47,303
And he doesn't say anything unnecessary.

1485
01:11:47,386 --> 01:11:49,221
That makes him even more attractive.

1486
01:11:49,972 --> 01:11:51,890
What will you do
when we get back to the dorm?

1487
01:11:51,974 --> 01:11:54,268
I wanna lie down for a bit.

1488
01:11:54,351 --> 01:11:56,437
- Let's check out the Post Office…
- Check it out?

1489
01:11:56,520 --> 01:11:57,980
…and see what gifts have been stocked.

1490
01:11:58,063 --> 01:11:59,398
I saw some new ones.

1491
01:11:59,481 --> 01:12:02,067
Wait a minute. Are you trying
to get a third gift out of me?

1492
01:12:03,027 --> 01:12:04,111
- No.
- Are you trying to?

1493
01:12:04,194 --> 01:12:06,989
- I'm not. I'm not.
- That kinda ruse won't work on me, okay?

1494
01:12:07,072 --> 01:12:08,699
- Are you sure?
- Oh, so cute.

1495
01:12:08,782 --> 01:12:11,160
- Oh, come on. Come on.
- Huh?

1496
01:12:11,243 --> 01:12:13,620
- No.
- What is this?

1497
01:12:13,704 --> 01:12:16,373
- No, I don't want to.
- You're so annoying.

1498
01:12:16,915 --> 01:12:19,418
I won't budge.
I march to the beat of my own drum.

1499
01:12:19,501 --> 01:12:20,961
Just to check it out.

1500
01:12:21,837 --> 01:12:25,090
I'll just look from the outside,
holding the doors open, like, "Oh, okay."

1501
01:12:25,174 --> 01:12:27,718
Fine, don't go. I'll still do what I want.

1502
01:12:27,801 --> 01:12:28,927
I might even turn evil.

1503
01:12:29,011 --> 01:12:30,721
I think he finds this behavior cute.

1504
01:12:30,804 --> 01:12:32,097
His eyes say he finds her cute.

1505
01:12:32,181 --> 01:12:33,432
Why should I have to do this for you?

1506
01:12:33,515 --> 01:12:35,434
I'm so annoying.
I know, I ask so much. Jeez.

1507
01:12:35,517 --> 01:12:37,519
The waves are coming again. Look.

1508
01:12:38,520 --> 01:12:40,481
I had a lot of fun on my date.

1509
01:12:40,564 --> 01:12:43,984
The conversation was great
and very natural.

1510
01:12:44,068 --> 01:12:45,569
I felt like we really clicked.

1511
01:12:45,652 --> 01:12:48,197
And he kind of played along well
no matter what I said,

1512
01:12:48,280 --> 01:12:50,908
so I felt like we really meshed.
We had a good time.

1513
01:12:51,575 --> 01:12:53,911
They seem compatible.
They have the same sense of humor.

1514
01:12:53,994 --> 01:12:55,788
If someone said to me,
"I'm not gonna tell you,"

1515
01:12:55,871 --> 01:12:57,539
I'd be like, "Tell me right now, damn it."

1516
01:12:57,623 --> 01:12:59,083
I couldn't play along with that.

1517
01:12:59,166 --> 01:13:00,292
This one's a done deal.

1518
01:13:00,376 --> 01:13:02,002
- Yeah, they're good.
- Ah, we've got one.

1519
01:13:02,795 --> 01:13:05,464
The conversation flowed really well,

1520
01:13:06,131 --> 01:13:08,425
and it wasn't all that bad.

1521
01:13:08,509 --> 01:13:09,843
However…

1522
01:13:09,927 --> 01:13:11,261
- Hmm?
- Hmm?

1523
01:13:11,345 --> 01:13:12,471
Anything you want to ask?

1524
01:13:12,554 --> 01:13:14,765
Why? Where is this coming from?

1525
01:13:15,349 --> 01:13:17,017
So there's nothing you want to ask me?

1526
01:13:17,101 --> 01:13:18,602
Why do you keep asking?

1527
01:13:18,685 --> 01:13:20,854
- These things happen naturally.
- Because I'm curious.

1528
01:13:20,938 --> 01:13:23,440
So, really nothing to ask?

1529
01:13:23,524 --> 01:13:27,236
Aren't you a little worried
we keep asking one another this?

1530
01:13:27,319 --> 01:13:29,822
Okay, Soo-hyun is just
being really awkward.

1531
01:13:29,905 --> 01:13:32,574
I don't think Soo-hyun can stand
the awkward pauses when things go silent.

1532
01:13:32,658 --> 01:13:34,910
- She can't stand the silence.
- Yeah, definitely.

1533
01:13:34,993 --> 01:13:38,664
I wore my running shoes today
in case they open the 5 Minute Library.

1534
01:13:38,747 --> 01:13:41,625
Everyone else was like,
"What shoes should I wear today?"

1535
01:13:41,708 --> 01:13:44,294
Take a pause, Soo-hyun.
Deep breath. Slow down.

1536
01:13:44,378 --> 01:13:47,172
I want to see the new releases.
Should I take a look?

1537
01:13:47,256 --> 01:13:49,842
See what it says?
But we don't know what we'll be doing.

1538
01:13:50,926 --> 01:13:53,470
I was a bit taken aback because…

1539
01:13:53,554 --> 01:13:56,932
the majority of the time,
Soo-hyun dominated the conversation.

1540
01:13:57,558 --> 01:14:00,394
Where do you usually hang out?
I can never find you when I come looking.

1541
01:14:00,477 --> 01:14:01,478
Me?

1542
01:14:01,562 --> 01:14:04,690
- I'm either alone or in my room.
- You're in your room?

1543
01:14:05,941 --> 01:14:07,985
That means I have to go
to your room to find you.

1544
01:14:08,068 --> 01:14:11,029
Why? Does that mean
you are curious about me?

1545
01:14:11,113 --> 01:14:15,117
Yeah. In fact yesterday, I seriously asked
Seo-yoon if I should go to your room,

1546
01:14:15,200 --> 01:14:16,535
and she was like, "Go!"

1547
01:14:17,995 --> 01:14:20,330
Tell her to relax… Eun-ji.

1548
01:14:20,414 --> 01:14:23,208
You see, I tell Seo-yoon everything.
Seriously, everything.

1549
01:14:23,292 --> 01:14:25,586
We literally talk until we fall asleep.

1550
01:14:25,669 --> 01:14:28,380
She told me that she'd been
going around looking for me,

1551
01:14:28,464 --> 01:14:31,842
and that felt to me like she was
kind of moving too fast,

1552
01:14:31,925 --> 01:14:35,220
which made me feel a little pressured.

1553
01:14:35,304 --> 01:14:39,057
But I figured since we seem to be
getting along so well,

1554
01:14:39,141 --> 01:14:41,226
I thought I should just deal with it.

1555
01:14:42,019 --> 01:14:44,396
- Oh, good, man. Nice.
- That's good. They're still good.

1556
01:14:44,480 --> 01:14:47,316
- It feels like we just dodged a bullet.
- That was a close one.

1557
01:14:47,399 --> 01:14:49,401
- He took it in stride.
- I couldn't even speak just now.

1558
01:14:49,485 --> 01:14:51,862
Him saying "I thought I should
just deal with it," that was good.

1559
01:14:51,945 --> 01:14:55,491
What a relief. Now that they've confirmed
that the interest is mutual,

1560
01:14:55,574 --> 01:14:58,118
Soo-hyun's naturally
a fast talker anyways,

1561
01:14:58,202 --> 01:14:59,578
but here, her speech is on rapid fire.

1562
01:14:59,661 --> 01:15:02,039
- She's saying whatever comes to mind.
- Exactly.

1563
01:15:02,122 --> 01:15:04,082
Clashes arise when the pace isn't in sync.

1564
01:15:04,166 --> 01:15:07,169
But at least Tae-hoon has made it clear

1565
01:15:07,252 --> 01:15:11,089
that he's willing to put up with it,
so let's see how it goes.

1566
01:15:11,632 --> 01:15:13,050
- Hyuk-joon and Han-ju.
- Hello.

1567
01:15:13,133 --> 01:15:14,843
Gosh, what is this date going to be like?

1568
01:15:14,927 --> 01:15:17,554
Oh, an umbrella.
Because I think it's going to rain.

1569
01:15:17,638 --> 01:15:20,057
I brought it just in case.
It was hailing earlier.

1570
01:15:20,140 --> 01:15:21,517
I heard.

1571
01:15:21,600 --> 01:15:22,726
So that's why.

1572
01:15:23,602 --> 01:15:25,979
I had high hopes for my date because

1573
01:15:26,063 --> 01:15:29,483
I went to the Post Office just before
I left for the date, and…

1574
01:15:33,111 --> 01:15:34,780
- What is it?
- A gift?

1575
01:15:34,863 --> 01:15:36,073
Wow, what is this?

1576
01:15:37,366 --> 01:15:39,368
There was a letter and a gift.

1577
01:15:39,451 --> 01:15:41,870
Someone gave him nutritional supplements.

1578
01:15:43,455 --> 01:15:45,541
It was signed anonymously.

1579
01:15:47,292 --> 01:15:51,588
But she said the fact that I tried
not to show I was sick

1580
01:15:51,672 --> 01:15:53,840
showed me in a positive light

1581
01:15:53,924 --> 01:15:56,134
instead of making me look frail.

1582
01:15:56,718 --> 01:15:59,096
I thought, "I know who this is from."

1583
01:15:59,179 --> 01:16:00,639
It's obviously Han-ju.

1584
01:16:01,348 --> 01:16:03,350
I'm really glad that we matched

1585
01:16:03,433 --> 01:16:06,103
and finally have this opportunity
to have this date.

1586
01:16:06,186 --> 01:16:08,939
Is this why he submitted Han-ju
as his desired date partner?

1587
01:16:10,440 --> 01:16:13,986
I've been hoping for
an opportunity to talk to you some more.

1588
01:16:14,861 --> 01:16:16,446
So yesterday I was debating

1589
01:16:16,530 --> 01:16:19,992
about whether to take you
or Jeong-eun for a ride

1590
01:16:20,075 --> 01:16:22,077
and then take you to the Sparks House.

1591
01:16:22,160 --> 01:16:23,161
Mmm.

1592
01:16:23,245 --> 01:16:27,082
I think it's still early in the process,
so I want to get to know you better now.

1593
01:16:28,000 --> 01:16:30,043
But when I was making the decision,

1594
01:16:30,127 --> 01:16:33,422
I figured that since you and I
already talked to each other a little,

1595
01:16:33,505 --> 01:16:36,174
it seemed the right thing to do was

1596
01:16:36,258 --> 01:16:39,219
to request a conversation
with Jeong-eun first.

1597
01:16:39,803 --> 01:16:41,722
And then today,

1598
01:16:41,805 --> 01:16:45,517
that would leave you and I
to go on a proper date.

1599
01:16:45,601 --> 01:16:47,352
So, yeah.

1600
01:16:47,436 --> 01:16:48,854
- Mmm.
- Yeah.

1601
01:16:48,937 --> 01:16:50,939
That's right. We only had
a Three-way Date together.

1602
01:16:51,023 --> 01:16:53,567
Yeah, exactly. And that format's
kind of uncomfortable.

1603
01:16:53,650 --> 01:16:54,651
That's right.

1604
01:16:55,319 --> 01:16:58,864
I thought it would be nice to get away
for a little and go do something.

1605
01:17:02,159 --> 01:17:04,411
Do you think a date off the grounds
is better?

1606
01:17:04,494 --> 01:17:06,747
- Yeah.
- Right? Yeah.

1607
01:17:06,830 --> 01:17:09,791
I've been thinking
I'd like to go with you, <i>oppa</i>,

1608
01:17:09,875 --> 01:17:11,335
if I got a chance to go on a date.

1609
01:17:12,377 --> 01:17:15,797
That makes me happy. I was smiling
ear to ear when we matched this morning.

1610
01:17:19,009 --> 01:17:23,096
Oh, this place has very nice vibes.
It's so unusual.

1611
01:17:24,306 --> 01:17:25,724
That's such a bright sweater.

1612
01:17:25,807 --> 01:17:29,436
Oh, yeah. You know,
with the weather all gloomy today,

1613
01:17:29,519 --> 01:17:33,607
I thought I should
brighten things up a little.

1614
01:17:33,690 --> 01:17:36,568
- That was a good choice. Yeah.
- Was it? You think so? Does it suit me?

1615
01:17:36,652 --> 01:17:39,404
- It totally suits you. Yeah. For sure.
- Yeah?

1616
01:17:42,824 --> 01:17:45,744
Before I left, I thought of
all these questions I wanted to ask you.

1617
01:17:45,827 --> 01:17:47,954
- But I forgot.
- Me too. But I've forgotten them too.

1618
01:17:48,038 --> 01:17:51,041
I know there was something specific
that I wanted to ask you.

1619
01:17:56,880 --> 01:18:00,425
It was good. "Before I left, I thought
of some questions to ask you."

1620
01:18:00,509 --> 01:18:03,845
I thought that was honestly
really quite cute

1621
01:18:03,929 --> 01:18:06,056
because it means that
she's been making an effort

1622
01:18:06,139 --> 01:18:07,432
and wants to communicate with me.

1623
01:18:07,516 --> 01:18:08,934
That made me feel good.

1624
01:18:12,229 --> 01:18:14,731
So, do you write letters very often?

1625
01:18:14,815 --> 01:18:19,319
Well, there aren't many opportunities
to write letters in daily life, right?

1626
01:18:19,403 --> 01:18:22,531
So, I wouldn't say I've written a lot, no.

1627
01:18:22,614 --> 01:18:24,574
Yeah, I find it really difficult.

1628
01:18:24,658 --> 01:18:26,243
Mmm. Why do you find it difficult?

1629
01:18:26,326 --> 01:18:29,037
- You're such a good talker.
- I'm a poor communicator.

1630
01:18:29,121 --> 01:18:30,872
- No, you're good.
- Really?

1631
01:18:31,415 --> 01:18:35,544
I've always found navigating
conversations a little difficult.

1632
01:18:35,627 --> 01:18:40,173
It doesn't matter if it's talking
or writing, I find them equally hard.

1633
01:18:40,841 --> 01:18:43,343
So, that's what my makeover
mainly focused on.

1634
01:18:43,427 --> 01:18:44,761
Oh, okay.

1635
01:18:44,845 --> 01:18:46,680
Wow, I see.

1636
01:18:46,763 --> 01:18:50,517
I find that quite surprising, actually.

1637
01:18:53,270 --> 01:18:57,524
Han-ju talked about herself
very openly and frankly.

1638
01:18:57,607 --> 01:19:00,819
And I found that to be
a very attractive quality.

1639
01:19:02,028 --> 01:19:06,032
So if you could go on another
one-on-one date in Jeju Island,

1640
01:19:06,116 --> 01:19:08,452
what would you like to do over there?

1641
01:19:08,535 --> 01:19:11,997
Mmm… Well, I told you
I like exhibitions, right?

1642
01:19:12,080 --> 01:19:15,167
And there's an art museum on Jeju Island,

1643
01:19:15,250 --> 01:19:16,793
so it'd be nice to go there.

1644
01:19:17,419 --> 01:19:19,421
What would you wanna do?

1645
01:19:19,504 --> 01:19:21,006
I wanna go to an <i>oreum</i>.

1646
01:19:21,089 --> 01:19:22,966
Oh, an <i>oreum</i>.

1647
01:19:23,049 --> 01:19:25,218
- Have you been to many? Which ones?
- Yes.

1648
01:19:25,302 --> 01:19:28,013
I think I've been to all of them. Yeah.

1649
01:19:28,096 --> 01:19:30,682
For me, there's one called Mundoji Oreum.

1650
01:19:30,766 --> 01:19:33,852
- I loved it there.
- Oh, I've never heard of it.

1651
01:19:33,935 --> 01:19:36,480
- Mmm! So I got there before you.
- Mundoji Oreum?

1652
01:19:36,563 --> 01:19:38,106
It's called Mundoji Oreum.

1653
01:19:38,190 --> 01:19:40,150
It's hard to get to, but it was amazing.

1654
01:19:40,233 --> 01:19:41,651
- Hmm.
- Is he smitten?

1655
01:19:41,735 --> 01:19:43,278
Has fate struck again?

1656
01:19:43,361 --> 01:19:46,782
Oh, and I think rivers are important.
Do you go to the Han River often?

1657
01:19:46,865 --> 01:19:49,576
I go there often. Quite often.

1658
01:19:49,659 --> 01:19:51,036
- I like rivers.
- Yes.

1659
01:19:51,119 --> 01:19:54,372
There's a reason
it attracts so many people to it.

1660
01:19:54,456 --> 01:19:58,126
I think I wrote down the Han River
is the place I wanted to go on a date.

1661
01:19:58,210 --> 01:19:59,419
Mmm.

1662
01:20:00,796 --> 01:20:02,088
Do you like walking?

1663
01:20:02,881 --> 01:20:06,134
- Walking? When the weather's nice.
- Right, when the weather's nice.

1664
01:20:06,218 --> 01:20:08,887
Would you say you go walking a lot?

1665
01:20:08,970 --> 01:20:11,014
Yeah, I really enjoy walking.

1666
01:20:12,098 --> 01:20:15,143
I think I'm most compatible
with Han-ju when it comes to hobbies.

1667
01:20:22,317 --> 01:20:23,610
Oh, we're in trouble.

1668
01:20:23,693 --> 01:20:25,737
This guy's ideal type changes
on the daily.

1669
01:20:25,821 --> 01:20:27,113
Choi Hyuk-joon!

1670
01:20:28,573 --> 01:20:30,200
Even if it's not a hobby of mine,

1671
01:20:30,283 --> 01:20:32,410
if there's something
the other person wants to do,

1672
01:20:32,494 --> 01:20:34,204
I'm usually willing to do it with them.

1673
01:20:34,287 --> 01:20:36,915
Basically, I just want to go
on normal dates.

1674
01:20:36,998 --> 01:20:39,000
It doesn't have to be anything
hugely special.

1675
01:20:39,084 --> 01:20:41,503
I'd be happy just getting coffee
with my girlfriend.

1676
01:20:41,586 --> 01:20:44,214
- I do not like karaoke.
- I know, right?

1677
01:20:44,297 --> 01:20:47,717
Seriously,
I sing, like, all my favorite songs.

1678
01:20:47,801 --> 01:20:49,803
What do you think of the Han River?

1679
01:20:49,886 --> 01:20:52,556
There are way too many bugs
flying around there.

1680
01:20:52,639 --> 01:20:54,808
Yeah, and I really hate flying insects.

1681
01:20:54,891 --> 01:20:58,562
I think I wrote down the Han River
as a place I wanted to go on a date.

1682
01:20:59,980 --> 01:21:03,275
When I asked Han-ju
whether she likes this or that,

1683
01:21:03,358 --> 01:21:05,360
she wasn't picky about anything.

1684
01:21:05,443 --> 01:21:08,280
It showed that she's easygoing,
which is really important to me.

1685
01:21:08,363 --> 01:21:10,949
She makes it seem like she'd be
happy anywhere, doing anything,

1686
01:21:11,032 --> 01:21:13,159
as long as we were together,
and I like that.

1687
01:21:13,243 --> 01:21:14,369
Yeah, man.

1688
01:21:14,452 --> 01:21:15,871
I used to believe in fate.

1689
01:21:15,954 --> 01:21:18,707
Matching with the same girl constantly
like it was meant to be,

1690
01:21:18,790 --> 01:21:20,292
that was really important to me.

1691
01:21:21,042 --> 01:21:24,671
But then I came to understand
how attraction stems from curiosity.

1692
01:21:26,089 --> 01:21:29,593
It's important to be curious.
And, frankly, I am curious

1693
01:21:29,676 --> 01:21:31,887
to how she will answer
to all these questions.

1694
01:21:31,970 --> 01:21:34,556
He's turning to the dark side.
What a disaster.

1695
01:21:34,639 --> 01:21:38,602
I think attraction
plus curiosity equals the perfect match.

1696
01:21:40,645 --> 01:21:42,939
Han-ju is my current top choice.

1697
01:21:43,690 --> 01:21:46,568
Where does Hyuk-joon stand
right now? Bring him over here.
